title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, molasses and egg; mix well.
Add cinnamon, ginger, cloves, baking soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Form a small ball.
Dip into granulated sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: In small glass dish (I use a pie pan), layer beans, sour cream, salsa, cheese and olives!
Garnish with chili powder sprinkled on top.
Serve cold.

title: cranberry nut pound cake
directions: Sift first seven ingredients and set aside.
Beat butter with next three ingredients until light and fluffy.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a double boiler and melt together. Then make your sandwiches.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Put mushrooms in wide mouth jar.
Pour dressing over to cover and refrigerate several
hours
or overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: tomato relish
directions: Boil, peel and mash tomatoes, then drain.
Chip peppers and onions.
Mix and cook slowly 1 hour.
Pour in pint jars and seal.

title: blueberry heaven(cold soup)
directions: Puree blueberries in blender until smooth.
Add milk, honey, cinnamon and 1/3 cup yogurt.
Puree well.
Pour mixture into a bowl and stir in remaining yogurt.
Cover bowl and chill thoroughly. Serve garnished with mint.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: potato cheese casserole(serves 8)
directions: Follow directions on flaked potato package.
Then add softened cream cheese.
Add into hot mashed potatoes.
Add beaten egg, onion, pimento, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Bake in a greased casserole (I use margarine).
This may be made a day ahead and refrigerated until needed.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour and shortening together.
Break egg into cup and beat.
Add water to make 1 cup and then mix in vinegar and salt. Add to flour mixture and blend with fork.
Seal dough in plastic bag and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Keeps for 2 months.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Add 1/2 tsp. baking soda, stirring until mixture is blended (will "rise").

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin cups.
In mixing bowl, combine egg or egg whites, skim milk, oatmeal and sugar.
Beat and slowly add dry ingredients.
Add melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: baked cornish hen with rice
directions: Combine celery and uncooked rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread onions over rice.
Top with Cornish hens, skin side up.
Bring water to a boil in a saucepan.
Add bouillon, seasonings and rice packet seasoning.
Stir until bouillon is dissolved.
Pour over hens.
Cover baking dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Brush hens with butter and bake, uncovered, for another 1/2 hour.

title: powdered walnut mini cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add all other ingredients in order given except for the 10x sugar.

title: homemade chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pan.
Add chili powder to taste.
Simmer until hot.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and stir.
Add 2 eggs and stir.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Add water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, potatoes and carrots.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooled cubed chicken and simmer 5 more minutes until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour in 1/2 cup milk.
Add to vegetables and chicken.
Add remaining 2 cups milk.
Cook until thickens.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Fry wings until very done and brown.
Drain on paper towel. Combine red wine vinegar, catsup, hot sauce and seasonings.
Set aside.

title: apple caramel dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Use apple slices to dip and enjoy!!

title: teresa's grandma's chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, mix first 5 ingredients.
Add milk.
Cook on low until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Let set.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cut sausage.
Put on top of rolls.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper and oregano together.
Pour mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream of pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in flour.
Brown chops on both sides.
Pour two cans of cream of chicken soup in cooking dish; put pork chops in soup and cover.
Cook at 250° for around three hours.

title: patti's berry topping
directions: Bring apple juice concentrate, cornstarch and salt to a boil; stir and cook until clear.	Add frozen berries and cook; stir until they	have
thawed
and
are	cooked.
Serve	over waffles, toast
or
in
tart
shells.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and berries.
Let stand until berries thaw. Drain juice and bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixed with butter and water.
Cook 2 minutes on low heat.
Cool slightly and pour into baked 8-inch pie shell.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: net's turkey seasoning
directions: Mix together and rub inside and outside of turkey.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all in a blender.

title: blueberry dumplings
directions: Cook berries and sugar with enough water to cover. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening until the texture of peas. Add milk and mix. Drop dumplings into boiling berry mixture and cook 10 minutes, uncovered, and 10 minutes, covered. Serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: baked turkey and dressing
directions: Salt and pepper turkey to taste and place in browning bag and bake until done, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: orange rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in very warm water in large mixing bowl.
Beat in 1/4 cup of the sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and 6 tablespoons of melted butter with mixer.
Gradually add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Knead in remaining flour.
Place in bowl and let rise until doubled (2 hours).
Knead dough on well floured surface about 15 times.
Roll 1/2 of the dough to circle.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and orange rind.
Brush dough with 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle with 1/2 the sugar and orange rind.
Cut into wedges. Roll up from wide end.
Repeat until all dough is used.
Place point down on greased pan.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni & english pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Mayonnaise
to taste. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 4 hours.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in milk, melted margarine, sugar, salt, lemon juice and vanilla.
Sift together cinnamon, flour and baking powder.
Stir into milk mixture just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Fold in apples.
Fill well-greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: fresh fruit pie(berries)
directions: Dissolve, stirring, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Blend together.
Add crushed berries.
Heat mixture slowly.
When just warm, add 1 teaspoon vinegar and continue heating until thickened and clear.
Place fresh berries in a baked pie shell; pour glaze over them.
Top with a meringue and brown quickly or top with whipped cream or any other whipped topping.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar and water and cook for 3 minutes. Add butter and enough powdered sugar to thicken; add nuts and spread over cookies.

title: peach-riesling sangria
directions: Mix in first 5 ingredients in large pitcher. Scrape in seeds from vanilla bean; add bean and stir to blend. Mix in fruit. Cover and chill overnight. Mix in ice and serve.

title: crab salad
directions: Remove any shell or cartilage from crabmeat.
Place all ingredients in bowl and mix together gently.
Serve on bed of lettuce along with fresh sliced Maryland tomatoes.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, cook pudding and milk according to package directions; cool.
In a large bowl, fold whipped topping into pie filling.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir gently. Fold in pudding.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yields 70 to 80 servings.

title: lazy man's cabbage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix in rice and onion soup. Chop cabbage and put in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Put beef mixture on top of cabbage.
Mix tomato soup and 1 can water together and pour over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions on package.
Add drained pineapple and shredded carrot.
Stir after adding ingredients and again, later, when Jell-O is partially congealed.
Serve on lettuce leaf with dollop of mayonnaise.
This can be put in a mold and served on a platter instead of in individual servings.

title: banana sour cream bars
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together for one minute.
Add bananas and vanilla and mix for one minute.
Add flour, salt, soda and nuts.
Mix for one minute (do not overmix).
Place in cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
For icing, cream remaining ingredients on high until fluffy.
A small amount of milk may be added to thin icing.
Spread over bars once they have cooled slightly.
Store in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 20 minutes longer.

title: festive fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Combine oil, eggs, and water in big bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir by hand until combined. Pour into pans and bake.
Remove from pan and cool.
Wrap in plastic or foil and store in refrigerator.
(If not all baked in one pan less time to cook required.)
Place in a well greased pan.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl (except chocolate syrup).
Blend to moisten, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour about 3/4 of batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Add 3/4 cup chocolate syrup to remaining batter; mix well. Pour over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done. Cool in pan.
Take out of pan; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Pull chicken apart. Mix all together. You can put a can of chicken broth or cream of chicken but not necessary. A lot of prayer, too. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn meal rolls
directions: Mix cornmeal,
salt
and
cold milk in pan.
Cook until very stiff.
Add sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast dissolved in lukewarm water.
Stir in flour to make medium dough.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Divide dough into 4 portions and roll
into	circle.
Cut
wedges from circle. Roll up beginning
with
wide
end.
Place	on greased baking sheets.
Let rise
for 45 minutes.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 425°.	Yields 32 rolls.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Put can of cranberries into Jell-O and melt.
Add cold water.
Pour into bowl; let set some in refrigerator, then add nuts and drained fruit cocktail. Mix.
If not set enough, stir again later.

title: deluxe candied potatoes
directions: Grease pan; put in layer of potatoes and oranges and a little orange juice.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg on each layer of potatoes; white or brown sugar may be used.
Slice stick of butter between layers of potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour in 375° oven.

title: ham twirls
directions: Place a ham slice on a plate and cover with cream cheese. Cut a top of the scallion to fit across the short end of the ham and roll up. Cut into slices and place on platter.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour (baking soda and cream of tartar, if using all-purpose flour).
Cover and refrigerate for at least two hours.

title: tortilla pizza for one
directions: Place tortilla on small pan or cookie sheet.
Spread oil on both sides and allow to soak in.
Put spaghetti sauce on tortilla and spread around.	Sprinkle a layer of cheese on sauce, but do not cover completely.
Put on toppings of your choice and another layer of cheese.
Put in oven or toaster oven on about 400° until cheese starts to turn brown.
Take out and let cool for about 5 minutes.
Cut in half and enjoy.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and
butter.
Add
eggs
and
vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add flour,
soda
and
oats; mix well.
Stir in peanuts. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with the dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with 1 slice of bacon (2 for very large breasts).
In a separate bowl, mix mushroom soup, sour cream and enough milk to make a thick sauce.
Pour over chicken and dried beef.

title: best ever sunday chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a plastic bag; shake to mix and set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and lemon juice; stir well.
Skin chicken, if desired.
Place 2 or 3 pieces in bag; shake well.
Dip in egg mixture, return to bag and shake again.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Pour oil to depth of 3/4-inch into a large skillet.
Fry 4 to 5 pieces in hot oil at 350°.

title: taco dip ii
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Mix in seasoning. Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with lettuce, cheese and tomato. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Place green beans in bottom of casserole dish. Put meat and soup in. Place Tater Tots on top. Put cheese of your choice on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat all the ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: maggie's oatmeal cookies(soft)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in margarine.
Add eggs and sugar. Combine oats and raisins separately.
Combine the rest of dry ingredients.
Mix all together.
Add raisins and oats last.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown, 10 to 14 minutes.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonful.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers in boiling water for about 5 minutes.
Then cool and stuff with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice from directions on package.
Set aside.
In a wok or frying pan, pour enough oil to cover bottom of pan; heat until hot.
Add meat and peppers, cooking until tender.
Add onions and lower heat.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook butter, milk, sugar and salt to soft ball stage.
Before taking from heat, add peanut butter and marshmallows.
Do not stir.
Cool.
Add vanilla and beat.
Pour into a well-greased plate, platter
or cookie sheet.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a bowl, mix butter, vermouth, parsley, lemon juice, garlic cloves, pepper and salt.
Place shrimp in shallow baking dish. Pour 3/4 mixture over shrimp.
Mix remaining portion with bread crumbs and scatter over shrimp.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: chocolate cream crunch
directions: Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar well until fluffy. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Blend well; spread over cooled crust. Chill well.
Combine chocolate pudding mix and milk until thick; pour over cream cheese crust.
Chill.
Combine vanilla pudding or butter pecan with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Beat until thick.
Pour over chocolate pudding in crust and frost with remainder of Cool Whip. Top with pecans.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Melt Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese in microwave until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Let cool for one hour in the refrigerator. Use as dip for fresh fruit.

title: cherry delight(very dietetic)
directions: Break up angel food cake into pieces and put in pan or deep bowl.
Mix vanilla pudding with cold milk until thick.
Whip in Cool Whip.
Pour over cake mix if you want it to cover the cake well.
Pour pie filling over cake mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread according to package directions.
Stir in Chilies, cumin, oregano and sage.
Bake in 8 inch square pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
In bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, and dressing mix.
Crumble 1/2 corn bread in a 13 by 9 inch pan.
layer with 1/2 beans, 1/2 mayonnaise mixture, 1/2 corn and tomatoes, green pepper, onion, bacon and cheese.
Repeat layer. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: popsicles
directions: Stir and fill popsicle containers and freeze.
Makes 24.

title: festive favorite
directions: Make 1 package Jell-O.
Let set until egg white consistency (not too liquidy, not too hard).
Mix in raspberries.
Pour into a 3-quart serving bowl.
Let set completely.
Mix softened cream cheese with sour cream.
Add in chopped walnuts.
Spread over set Jell-O.
In separate bowl, make second package Jell-O.
Let set until egg white consistency.
Add in yogurt.
Mix or whisk well. Pour over sour cream mixture.
Chill 4 hours.
An absolute favorite!
Serves 4 to 6.
Double ingredients for 12 servings.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well salad dressing or mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, vinegar and onion.
Pour over broccoli, cauliflower, peas and Cheddar cheese.
Mix until well coated.

title: lazy-day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water following package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine oregano with spaghetti sauce.

title: zesty italian casserole
directions: Cook as directed on box.
Add 1/2 cup cottage cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
May need more flour to make a soft dough.
May add other spices such as cinnamon, etc.
Cut out and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salt water until tender.
Remove meat from bone and chop fine.
Combine crumbs, onion and 1/2 of the eggs in large mixing bowl.
Pour broth over ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in bottom of baking dish.
Place layer of chicken and other egg over mixture.
Pour cream of chicken soup on top.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: luscious pineapple cream pie
directions: Add lemon juice to milk and stir well.
Add pineapple, nuts and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Place in crust.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Top with remaining Cool Whip and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix and boil to form a soft ball in cold water.
Stir quickly.
This is set and will get hard, so watch as it thickens. This works well on apple cake.

title: broiled pepper chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; cut each breast into halves.
Mix oil, marjoram, red pepper, margarine and salt; brush chicken on both sides with margarine mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down, on rack in broiler pan.
Set oven control to broil or 550°.
Broil chicken with tops 7 to 9 inches from heat for 30 minutes.
Turn; broil until brown and thickest pieces are done, 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown your ground beef and drain.
Cut up cheese into pieces. Put all the ingredients into crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cook on high for 1 hour, stirring occasionally or until the cheese melts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out thin.
Bake at 375° for 10 or 12 minutes.
Use any favorite cut-outs.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover with Saran Wrap and chill overnight.

title: speedy peach pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and baking powder; add egg, milk, vanilla and hot melted oleo.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch buttered Pyrex dish.
Add 2 cups or 1 can juicy peaches.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: deer nuggets
directions: Soak deer meat overnight in ice cold salt water.
Cut deep meat, cross grain, into 3/4 ounce pieces.
Put flour, seasoned salt and pepper into container together; stir or shake until well blended.
Mix milk and lemon juice together; pour over deer and stir until all pieces of meat are well moistened, then drain off excess liquid.
Stir or shake meat in flour mixture until all pieces of meat are well covered in flour.
Drop pieces of meat into deep cooking oil at 325° to 350°.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef in large frying pan; drain grease.
Add Ragu sauce, salt, pepper, garlic and red peppers to taste.
Let simmer while noodles cook.
Slice Mozzarella cheese (thin).
Drain noodles; place in cold water.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in apples alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts if desired.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream or frost.

title: toffee square
directions: Cream margarine and sugar then blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.

title: picnic potato squares
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup milk in saucepan.
Place over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, adding potatoes, carrots, celery and pickles last.
Pour into pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cherry bonbons
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts. Take small amount of dough, flatten out in palm of hand and place cherry in center.
Bring dough up around and roll in the palms of your hand to form a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and cold milk together.
Add sweetened condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding. Chill and serve.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in boiling water until tender.
Stir in mixture of sugar and flour; cook after mixture begins to boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts, grated lemon rind and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried onion rings(eggplant, cauliflower or shrimp)
directions: Combine milk, egg and oil.
Stir in flour, mixing well.
Allow batter to stand 15 minutes.

title: modeling clay
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Store it in an airtight plastic container.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and flour.
Add extract; blend well.
Spread batter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch loaf pan.
Cut surface of batter to make 24 squares.
Spoon filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Cool and remove squares from pan.

title: opera fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2 quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar, milk, cream, corn syrup and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Immediately remove from heat.
Cool until lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Beat vigorously until mixture becomes very thick and starts to lose its gloss.
Quickly stir in cherries or nuts or both and pour into a buttered shallow pan or platter.
Mark while warm.
Cut when firm.

title: supremes de volailles vallee d'auge
directions: Skin, bone, trim and cut a pocket in the cutlet.
Stuff each with a small slice of cheese.
Press the edges closed.
Butter a baking dish; set cutlets in it.
Sprinkle them with salt and pepper and a little lemon juice; cover them with buttered parchment paper.
Bake the cutlets in a 475° preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: carolyn's broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Add salt, pepper and Accent to taste.
Mix in remaining ingredients well.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Add buttered Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: sadie's salsa
directions: Toast taco mix on a cookie sheet on low heat.
(Watch this closely, it burns easily.)
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: "make me feel good" chicken soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil in saucepan.
In bowl, mix beaten egg and Cream of Wheat together.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls into boiling broth and boil for 1 minute.
Add parsley and serve.

title: chicken, broccoli, dressing
directions: Saute garlic, onion and mushrooms in some olive oil.
Then add cut up chicken breasts without skin.
Cook for 10 minutes or so. Add Worcestershire sauce to this while cooking.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook the broccoli per direction on box.

title: chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef, onion, celery, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in kidney beans, the undrained tomatoes, the tomato sauce, water, chili powder, salt, basil and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp dip and spread
directions: Rinse shrimp
with
cold water;
drain, then mix shrimp and remaining ingredients together.
Serve on crackers.

title: seco de gallina(chicken)
directions: Cut the chicken into pieces and fry in shortening until golden brown.
Add onions.
When brown, add tomatoes, peppers and the rest of the seasonings.
Pour in the orange juice.
Add hot sauce and simmer for an hour or more until the chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients first.
Mix with sauerkraut.
Add other ingredients and toss.
Refrigerate overnight in container with tight cover.
Stores 2 to 3 weeks.
Run cold water over sauerkraut to remove salt.
Drain good before using.

title: doris' ham loaf
directions: In a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, combine the butter and brown sugar. Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of the juice.
Spread the pineapple over the butter and brown sugar.
Combine the reserved juice and the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Press into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Invert the loaf to serve.
Serves 6.

title: susan's baked corn
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish. Mix all ingredients in one bowl except cheese. Layer corn mixture and cheese, ending with cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Add salt and flour. Add soda to sour cream.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir well.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Chill overnight; roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness on floured board.
Cut out.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Lift with spatula to remove cookies.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the warm water; add the yeast.
Stir and let rest about 5 minutes.
Mix in the oil, egg and flour and stir until well mixed.
Preheat the oven to 425°.
Grease muffin tins. Because this is a really soupy mixture, spoon into muffin tins. Bake for about 20 minutes.
The batter keeps well in the refrigerator for a week.

title: honey poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine ingredients; shake well.
Use over fresh red leaf lettuce with avocado and grapefruit sections.

title: pumpkin oatmeal loaf
directions: Combine oats, dates, raisins, pecans and milk.
Mix well and gradually stir into oatmeal mixture.
Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° about an hour or until comes clean with a toothpick.

title: bologna or ham salad
directions: Grind together bologna or ham and eggs.
Mix Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar and milk in small bowl.
Add pickle relish.
Pour over meat; mix well.

title: 3 layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Spread evenly on bottom.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly, sprinkle coconut over cracker crumbs and pour milk over coconut.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lentil and brown rice soup
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, place the lentils, rice, oil, garlic, onion, carrot, celery, tomato, stock, wine, soy sauce, bay leaf, basil, paprika and thyme.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place over high heat and bring the mixture to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer the soup, covered, for about 45 minutes, or until the rice and lentils are cooked, but not mushy.
Correct the seasonings and serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in bottom of casserole pan.
Mix sour cream, 1/2 cup butter, cheese, onion and soup together.
Spread over top of hash browns.
Crush corn flakes and sprinkle over top of mixture.
Pour the other 1/2 cup melted butter over top of everything.
Cook uncovered for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Stir in flour, apples and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Bake in a greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and cream together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add sifted flour alternating with sweet milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before removing from pan. Use large Bundt pan.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake cake as directed on package for 13 X 9 inch pan.
Cool 20 minutes.
Poke top of warm cake every 1/2 inch with handle of wooded spoon.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk evenly over the top of the cake. (Let this stand until milk has been absorbed by cake.)
Drizzle with caramel topping.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Spread whipped topping over top of cake.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is done.
Add other ingredients and mix together, except noodles.
When all ingredients are mixed well, turn noodles over lightly until mixed.
Try not to break noodles.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° with cover for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Grated cheese can be added to top when done.

title: 3-hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 tablespoon lukewarm water.
Add 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Heat milk.
Remove from fire.
Add butter to cool.
Add milk and butter to eggs and sugar. Beat and add yeast.
Add sifted flour to mixture.
Let rise until double.
Knead and cut out.
Dip in butter.
Place in pan.
Let rise again.
Bake.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the shortening, sugars and eggs.
In separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
To this mixture, now add the cornflakes, oatmeal, pecans and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: red, white and blueberry delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press on bottom of 12 x 7-inch dish.
In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon, yogurt, marshmallows and nuts.
Spread half over crust.
Top with half berry mixture, remaining yogurt mixture, then remaining berries.
Cover.
Freeze for 6 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Freeze leftovers.
Great fourth of July dessert!
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pinwheels
directions: Dry dill pickles with paper towels.
Put creamed cheese around pickles, then wrap the ham around the cheese covered pickle.
Put in freezer for 10 minutes until cheese is firm.
Remove from freezer and slice in 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices and place on serving tray.
These are great for appetizers.

title: swizzle sticks
directions: Wrap one slice of bacon around each bread stick.
Roll in parmesan.
Place seams down on a well greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.
Serve and enjoy!

title: frosting for gingerbread house
directions: Combine.
Beat 5 to 10 minutes.
Store in an airtight container, as it gets hard.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend on high until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: party salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together; let stand 1 hour. Add all other ingredients; stir in Cool Whip mixture. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: ziggie's cake with frosting
directions: Cake:
Mix flour, sugar, eggs, baking soda, salt, nuts and pineapple well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, egg yolks, brown sugar, salt and spices; add milk.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff; fold into pumpkin mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°; bake for 30 minutes longer or until pie tests done.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine and sugar in heavy pan, add chopped fruit and cook 3 minutes.
Add eggs, slowly cook 2 minutes.
Cool and add rest of the ingredients.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix Bisquick and granulated sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over baked layer.
Bake until set, about 25 minutes.
Loosen edges from sides of pan while warm. Cool completely; cut into about 1 1/2 inch squares.
Store in loosely covered container.
Makes 4 dozen squares.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water; let cool.
Mash cheese; add pineapple, celery, pimiento and nuts.
Mix this into jello and put in refrigerator until begins to gel.
Whip cream and fold into jello.

title: walnut raisin spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Stir well.
Add pecans and pour into crust.
Bake for 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add 1/3 cup mixture to beef and remaining ingredients, except cheese (may be omitted.)
Mix together.
Spread 1/4 cup soup mixture over loaf.
Make a gravy with drippings and remaining soup mixture.
Last 5 minutes add cheese to melt (if desired.)

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Spread mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake in 350° preheated oven for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut in squares.
Serve warm as a snack or with meal.
Makes 20.

title: waffles
directions: Beat mixture thoroughly with 1/2 cup melted butter added in at the end.
Pour small amounts onto waffle iron, cooking until golden brown.

title: country-style chicken dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine frozen potatoes and 1/2 can French fried onions. In a small bowl, blend soup and milk.
Pour half over the potato mixture. Arrange cheese slices over potato mixture.
Top with chicken, skin side down.

Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes. Stir vegetables into potatoes and turn chicken pieces over. Bake 20 minutes, uncovered. Stir potato mixture and top chicken with remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: spring carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 3 x 1/4-inch strips.
Combine carrots and water in saucepan.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Combine pineapple, cornstarch, ginger and nutmeg in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Add pineapple mixture to carrots.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant.
Lay on side and slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Mix beaten egg and water.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Dip eggplant slices in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry eggplant until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
In an oblong baking dish or pan, about 11 x 7-inch, layer spaghetti sauce, eggplant and cheese.
Sprinkle with Italian seasonings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: To make the syrup, mix together the first 4 ingredients until they are dissolved.
Use 1 cup or more of syrup per 9-inch pie shell.
Then mix the remaining ingredients to crumb consistency. Pour the syrup into unbaked pie crusts and divide the crumbs over top.
Bake them for 10 minutes at 450°, for 30 minutes more at 375°, then for 30 minutes longer at 350°.
This recipe makes 4 pies.

title: spicy "hoppin" john soup
directions: Soak peas in water overnight or bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain tomatoes, reserve liquid, then chop tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and liquid to peas.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice and meat.
Cover and cook on low heat 3 to 4 hours or until peas are tender.
Dice cooked meat and return to peas.
Add cooked rice, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve.
It's delicious!

title: italian chicken pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Cook asparagus, tomatoes, garlic, bell pepper and onion in broth in 10-inch skillet over medium heat 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly, until asparagus is crisp-tender and chicken is no longer pink in center.
Stir in spaghetti and remaining ingredients.
Toss about 30 seconds or until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to hard boil; let bubble for a few minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the butter; let melt.
Add the baking soda; stir until frothy.
Pour over popped corn.
Form into balls.
Makes 16 medium balls.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all well.
Place in 8 x 8-inch square pan and freeze.
Cut in squares.
May be used as dessert or salad.

title: toffee bars
directions: Thoroughly cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Press mixture into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
While still warm, cut into bars or squares.
Cool before removing from pan. Yields 3 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix everything together, including bacon grease.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rosemary potatoes(healthy eating section)
directions: Wash potatoes and slice in wedges (leaving skin on).
Spread out in baking dish (such as one 13 x 9 1/2-inch).
Add ingredients and spray generously with nonstick cooking spray (preferably one with a butter flavor).
Cover with Saran Wrap and put in microwave oven on High for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake in 475° oven for 45 minutes, stirring often.

title: no-fat beans
directions: Pick over and rinse beans.
Put in 4-quart pot with water to cover.
Bring to a boil. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Drain.
Add stock or water.
Bring to a boil. Turn heat to medium-low and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours until tender.
Add remaining ingredients halfway through cooking time.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken pieces, skinned side up, in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place onion slices on chicken.
Pour salsa over chicken.
Bake for 60 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear, basting occasionally.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: squash rice casserole
directions: Put rice in a pan; put water in pan to just cover rice.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan and layer ingredients in order given (may use more water if need be).
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until rice is done.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix the ingredients and press onto pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Drop with spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine cheese and tomatoes (with all liquid) in a microwavable bowl.
Heat on full power, stirring every 2 minutes until melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: diane's mom's microwave fudge
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Microwave (uncovered) on High for 7 to 12 minutes, stirring 3 times during cooking.
Remove carefully with mitts. Stir in chocolate chips until melted. Blend in Marshmallow Creme and peppermint extract, if desired.
Pour into buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Chill until set. Cut into squares.

title: tropical fruit yogurt shake
directions: In a blender, combine banana pieces with pineapple juice, yogurt, kiwi fruit and ice.
Secure lid and process until blended. Pour into chilled glasses and serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: oven-crisp eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
On a piece of waxed paper, blend crumbs, oregano, paprika and salt.
Set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Then egg, melted butter, water and vinegar.
Mix well until it has elasticity, then roll out for 2 (9-inch) pie tins.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie plates.

title: pre-civil war plantation pudding delight
directions: Cover fruit with sugar and then make batter by creaming butter with sugar.
Add flour sifted with baking powder.
Add the fruit. Cover with boiling water.
(Batter will rise to the top while baking.)
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour until firm and lightly brown.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir all dry ingredients in.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in pan.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cabbage with bacon
directions: Chop cabbage and bacon and cook until cabbage is transparent in a large saucepan.
Saute onions until golden brown.
Add onions, vinegar, water, salt and pepper to taste to the cabbage and bacon.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve.

title: wassail(drink for good health)
directions: Boil first three ingredients for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Take off heat and add tea bags.
Brew for 5 to 10 minutes; strain mixture.
Take out cloves and cinnamon sticks (save for potpourri).
Add sugar, lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Stir until sugar dissolves.

title: marinated swordfish
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Place fish in bowl. Let marinate at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.

title: tex-mex ground turkey potato boats
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise in half.
Scoop out center of each potato to within 1/4-inch of potato skin.
Reserve potato for other use.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover the beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain the water; cover the beans again with water and parboil.
Remove the beans; place in casserole.
Mix the water, sugar and molasses. Pour over beans.
Place in a 300° oven for several hours.
A crock-pot may be used.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix well the butter, sugar, egg, almond extract and vanilla. Set aside.
In another bowl, mix flour and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Blend red food coloring in one half.
Roll 1 teaspoon each of red dough and white dough on a lightly floured board into 4-inch long strips.
Place side by side; pinch bottom ends lightly together and twist to form a cane. Press top ends together.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
While still warm, sprinkle with a mixture of 1/2 cup crushed peppermint candy and 1/2 cup sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Boil
noodles;	grease	baking	dish;
mix
eggs, milk, seasoning and cheese; add to noodles.
Put in dish and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Can also put cheese on top to bake.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Remove from oven.
Brush with melted butter or margarine.
Cool and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender. Stir in cream cheese until melted. Add soups, milk, salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Stir until smooth and thoroughly heated. Garnish and serve.

title: acuff steak house banana pudding
directions: Mix well and layer with bananas and vanilla wafers. Delicious.

title: chicken-and-shrimp florentine
directions: Peel and
devein
shrimp;
set aside.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper and garlic powder; place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking
pan.
Dot
with 2 tablespoons butter and pour wine over top. Broil 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned, turning once. Add
shrimp; broil 5 to 8 minutes more or until shrimp turns pink,
stirring
once.
Remove
from
oven, cool slightly.	 Drain drippings
and
reserve.	Cut
chicken
in bite-size pieces, set chicken and shrimp aside.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt the butter in the oven. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Bake at 350° or 325° for a glass pan. Cool. Cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Melt jello in boiling water. Put 1 cup of ice,
into hot jello, stir until jello is thick. Remove any ice chips that have not melted. Mix in cool whip and strawberries. Pour into pie shell and freeze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Crush bananas and whip until very light.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, then flour, soda and chopped nuts.
Add bananas. Turn into greased bread tin.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole(main dish)
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and cut into chunks.
Place meat in a greased casserole pan (size of lasagne dish).
Top with mushrooms.
Mix milk, soup and sour cream and pour on top of meat and mushrooms.
Make stuffing according to directions on bag. Place on top of meat mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground chuck; add Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Continue stirring until cheese has melted, and mixture is creamy. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cube, cook and drain potatoes.
Mash while hot.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, margarine and onions.
Place in casserole dish, then cover with melted butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven until browned lightly and is bubbly (400° oven for 3 minutes).
This makes 1 large casserole or 2 regular casseroles, or ingredients can be halved.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until mixture spins a thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook until light brown.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda.
Beat.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet and shake until spread out.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix broccoli and all other ingredients together; pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas.
Pour in greased casserole dish. Pour undiluted soup and cheese on top.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nannie's luncheon salad(is easily expanded to serve an indefinite number.)
directions: Place cantaloupe wedge on lettuce bed.
Arrange shrimp on top of wedge and cover with curried mayonnaise.
Garnish with halved grapes.

title: salmon bake
directions: Spread salmon in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Fold in the next 3 ingredients.
Blend 1 tablespoon butter with flour in saucepan until smooth; add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in paprika and egg. Fold into salmon mixture.
Spread bread cubes over casserole; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: granola cereal
directions: In large roaster, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Combine almond flavoring, honey and oil.
Pour oil mixture over dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread on 3 cookie sheets.
Bake in a 250° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on tray.
Stir well and store tightly covered.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese; place in greased dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hog head cheese
directions: Clean head.
Cover with water.
Cook until meat falls off bone.
Grind meat.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pack in a loaf pan.
Put weight onto mold.
Let set until set.
Unmold and slice.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cut cookie dough into 9 equal pieces, then cut these into 36 pieces.
Place 1 piece of dough in each (miniature) muffin cup. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Unwrap candy; remove cookies from oven.
Immediately press candy in center of each cookie.
Allow to cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Carefully remove and place on paper towel to cool.
Yield: 36 cookies.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Place potatoes, onions and egg whites in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potato mixture and toss lightly.

title: meat pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, and garlic in large skillet.
Pour off excess grease.
Add mixed vegetables and evaporated milk. Reserve.
Bake bottom pie crust for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add mixture and place top crust.
Vent crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Bring water, peppers and ham to a boil in a large nonstick skillet.
Stir in yellow rice mix.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir in peeled, deveined medium-size shrimp and box of frozen cut okra.
Cover and cook 7 minutes, stirring a few times, or until shrimp are pink and opaque in center and rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Beat cream cheese and drained pineapple juice until creamy. Add pineapple. Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip and mix well. Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat potatoes, cream, lemon peel, juice, spices and egg yolks until smooth.
Reserve 1/3 cup coconut; fold remaining coconut into sweet potato mixture.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually beat in brown sugar to make a stiff meringue.
Fold into sweet potato mixture.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with coconut and almonds.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 55 minutes or until inserted knife blade comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Measure and sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to first mixture. Then add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Mix together well.
Pour in a tube pan and bake at 300° for 55 minutes.

title: honey mustard
directions: Mix above ingredients and chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients and bake in tube pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion, bell pepper and tomatoes until done; drain.
Add salt and chili powder.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Add to sausage mixture; then add milk and sour cream. Pour all into baking dish.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: appetizer spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls (no larger) and bake immediately or freeze on a cookie sheet.
Store frozen balls in a plastic bag.
Bake 15 minutes at 325° or 30 minutes if frozen.
Yields about 8 dozen balls.

title: strawberry-lemon cake
directions: Bake our lemon velvet cake mix in layers as directed.
Cool. Blend 1 package of our creamy white frosting mix with 3 tablespoons soft butter and 1/4 cup mashed, fresh strawberries or 1/4 cup thawed, frozen strawberries.
Beat until smooth, creamy and fluffy.
Use to fill and frost cake.
Decorate top of cake with 6 to 8 fresh whole strawberries.

title: spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Drain well on paper towel.
Crumble. Rinse spinach carefully.
Drain well.
Tear spinach into a salad bowl.
Clean and slice mushrooms.
Cut lemon into thin wedges. Rinse radishes.
Slice thinly.
Cut eggs into wedges.
Add mushrooms, lemons and radishes to spinach.
Blend.
Garnish salad with the egg wedges.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Add oil-vinegar dressing.
May also be served with this salad.
Preparation time 30 minutes.

title: velvet cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Add sour cream to creamed mixture and add dry ingredients.
Stir in maraschino cherries and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: In a bowl, beat together the butter and powdered sugar until smooth and creamy. Add vanilla.
Blend the flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add this mixture to batter and blend well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Roll dough out into 2 balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least 1 hour. Flatten dough out and cut into 15 to 16 equal size pieces. Shape into small logs about the size of your little finger.
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm but not brown.
While warm, roll into powdered sugar.
Let cool and roll again.

title: cold strawberry soup
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Puree.
If fresh strawberries are used, refrigerate for at least two hours.
If you use frozen berries, it can be served immediately.
Serve in soup bowls.
Garnish with fresh mint.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg, the 2 cups warm water, salt and 4 cups of flour.
Mix and add yeast/water mixture.
Beat about 4 to 5 minutes with mixer.
Add rest of flour slowly until stiff dough or add by hand.
Turn onto board and knead 4 to 5 minutes.
Place in greased Tupperware or bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. Make into rolls and place in greased pan.
Let rise 3 to 4 hours. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh tomato vinaigrette
directions: Combine tomato, onion, sugar, vinegar, basil and salt in blender. Process until blended. With blender running, slowly add the combined oils.
Refrigerate.

title: french onion soup
directions: Prepare dry toasted French bread.
Then heat butter and oil in a 4-quart pan over medium-low heat.
Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft and caramel-colored but not browned (30 to 40 minutes).
Stir in flour and cook for 2 minutes to brown lightly.
Pour in about 1 cup of the broth, stirring to blend flour and broth.
Add remaining broth, water and wine.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Pour into 9-inch square baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and tests done.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
Remove fat and add next five ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes, uncovered, and stir occasionally.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Combine rest, except Mozzarella.

title: raspberry rave
directions: Have 8 to 10-cup Bundt pan ready.
Drain raspberries and pineapple in sieve.
Press fruit to get 2 cups liquid; set aside. Bring 1 cup water to boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in 2 cups reserved liquid from fruit.
Stir in drained fruit and sour cream until blended.
Pour in Bundt pan and refrigerate 8 hours until firm.
Unmold.

title: joshua's favorite chili
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion in skillet.
Blend seasoning salt and garlic powder; season to taste.
Drain off grease, leaving just a little for moisture.
Pour contents into 8 or 10-quart pot. Add kidney beans, tomato juice and water.
Stir and heat; bring to a boil.
Simmer.
Add butter and chili powder.
Let simmer 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with rolls or rice.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind up in meat grinder the eggs, Colby cheese and ham, then add cream cheese and 2 dashes of Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Roll in parsley flakes.
Mold with hands like you would a meat loaf.
Serve with crackers.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Drain potatoes and mash.
Add diced eggs, onion and pickles.
Add 1 package Sweet 'N Low and mix with mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients, then add dry ingredients, alternating with wet ingredients.
Batter is very thin.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until it tests done.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir until smooth the first 4 ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.
Raisins may be used instead of chocolate chips.

title: ranch cucumber salad
directions: Add prepared Ranch dressing to cover. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and chili powder to taste.
Lay six tortillas in a large, greased casserole dish.
Spoon meat over.
Place half of cheese slices on top.
Spread beans over and cover with remaining tortillas. Dilute soup with water and spoon over casserole.
Top with rest of cheese.
Mash tomatoes and pour on top of casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 15 to 30 minutes before serving.
If tortillas are frozen, thaw before using.
(An 8 to 10 ounce package of Doritos can be used instead of tortillas.)

title: happy bacardi pina colada cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except coconut in a large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes in mixer.
Pour in oblong 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: mock chicken salad
directions: Wash tuna in strainer with hot water.
Add enough water to soup to equal 2 cups.
Boil and add dry jello.
When cool, add to remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into mold or an oblong glass dish.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: mary baber's kifli nut rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into flour and mix well.
Then cut in lard and oleo as for pie dough.
Beat egg yolks and egg.
Add to dough. Then add milk until you work it into a ball.
Grease bowl, put in dough and turn so top will be greased.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Beat eggs until light, stir in sugar, oil, zucchini, and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and then the nuts.
Pour into greased pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: john benghetti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion, pepper, peas and 3 cans of soup.
Add noodles (which have been cooked and drained) and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cheese, cut up.
Pour into large casserole and top with more chopped cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad(makes 16 servings)
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti (run cool water over to cool down). Add spaghetti to all vegetables. Mix in Salad Supreme and salad dressing. Refrigerate for at least 5 hours before serving.

title: raisins bars(diabetic)
directions: In a small saucepan, bring raisins, apple juice and shortening to a boil. Remove from heat and cool. Mix remaining ingredients, except nuts. Stir into raisin mixture. (Then, mix in nuts, if desired.) Spray an 8-inch square nonstick baking pan with cooking spray. Spread dough evenly in pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool. When cooled, cut into 2-inch bars. (May be stored in a tightly covered container.) Makes 16 bars, 75 calories each (85 calories each with nuts).

title: almond roca candy
directions: Sprinkle half of the nuts on bottom of cookie sheet (with sides), then sprinkle half of the chocolate on top. Cook butter and sugar to 350°, stirring constantly.
This is just to the point of burning and gives a caramel flavor.
Pour mixture over chocolate and sprinkle rest of chocolate and then nuts. Break into pieces when cool.

title: nellie's cornbread
directions: Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased cake pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly tender; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Place chicken on top. (Optional: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.)
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Melt margarine; add crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: churros
directions: Bring water, lemon juice, salt and 1 tablespoon oil to a boil. Add flour all at once and stir until dough is thick and smooth. Let dough cool and then put in a churrera or cake decorator with a hole about 1/2-inch wide.
Dough is dropped into hot oil, each churro being about 4-inches long.
(Test oil first, if oil is not hot enough, churros will separate; if too hot, they'll burn.
Use first churro to test.)
Churros are done when golden brown.
Allow oil to drain well from churros.
Sprinkle with sugar and serve hot.
Great with hot chocolate.

title: cresha(italian cheese bread)
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs and melted butter, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Dissolve yeast in warm milk and sugar. Then stir into egg mixture.
Knead as for bread.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Make small or large loaves and let rise again. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
If using small pans, a little less time is needed.
Be sure it has a healthy tan crust.
Enjoy with a meal or between meal snack.
Delicious when toasted.
This is always served for Easter.

title: dumplings
directions: Pour flour in a bowl and season to taste with garlic, salt and pepper.
Add enough milk to make a dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; roll out thin.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch strips and then cut strips into 1-inch rectangles.
When chicken broth is boiling, add dumplings and cook a couple of minutes.
This can be doubled or halved.

title: easy party punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aids and sugar in water.
Add frozen juices and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In skillet over low to medium heat, saute garlic about 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes. Serve over spaghetti or seafood.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over chicken or meat.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: golden cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and Equal in large bowl with whisk until smooth.
Gently fold in Dream Whip; put in refrigerator. Pour 1 cup milk in bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat with whisk until blended, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk; mix well.
Use a graham or baked pie shell; spread cream cheese mixture over bottom of pie shell.
Spread pumpkin mixture over cream cheese mixture.
Chill in refrigerator. Layers can be put in pie dish with no pie shell to cut down on calories.
Will cut out even with no shell.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until sugar dissolves.
Add peanut butter; stir in noodles.
Drop on waxed paper to cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chocolate refreshers
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Combine dates, sugar, water and butter in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat until it begins to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate morsels. Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with juice and milk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake on a large cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crunch muffins
directions: Combine Wesson oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix in mixer; add vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Dice apples and mix with flour.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Raisins can be added.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth. Beat egg whites stiff; fold into cream cheese mixture. Combine 3/4 of graham cracker crumbs and butter; cover bottom of greased 9-inch tube pan with crumb mixture. Pour cake mixture on top of crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until slightly brown. Remove from oven.

title: philippine egg roll
directions: In 2 tablespoons of hot oil, brown garlic.
Add onion, then the ground meat.
Cook 5 minutes on high heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat.
Stir in green beans.
Cook for one minute. Then add grated carrots.
Stir and cook for one minute.
Add soy sauce and bean sprouts.
Cook for 1 minute.
Cool it off.

title: corn fritter bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: loaf cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until done.

title: italian pasta
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
In a large bowl, combine spaghetti sauce and spices.
Add cooked pasta. Stir well.
Add cheeses.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: strawberry gelatin dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water; do not add cold water. Combine all ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into bowl and let gel in refrigerator.
Leave the remaining 1/2 at room temperature.
After the mixture gels, place the sour cream over the jello evenly.
Pour the remaining jello over this and let gel until firm.

title: coconut loaf cake
directions: Note:
This recipe is very old and calls for a moderately heated oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, eggs, celery, pimentos, onion, mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and salt.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, add cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. This is my family's favorite.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add spices and sauce.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add milk.
In a 2-quart casserole layer beef and add macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry candy
directions: Chop or grate cranberries.
Place cranberries, orange peel and orange juice in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil slowly for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add gelatin and sugar.
Cook for 10 to 12 minutes or until you can see pan bottom when spoon is drawn across mixture. Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Spread mixture into well buttered 5 x 9-inch pan.
Let stand, uncovered, for at least overnight.
Cut into squares.
Let stand, uncovered, to dry.
May take 12 to 24 hours to dry.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt.
Blend with the beaten
egg yolks. Add
milk,
lemon
juice and rind, beating thoroughly. Melt butter
and
add.
Fold
in stiffly beaten egg whites and bake in pudding
dish
set in pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 3/4 hour.
Serve cold.
Serves 6.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Add water to cocoa mixture.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring.
Add 2 1/2 cups more water to cocoa mixture.
Cover saucepan and place over low heat.
Heat to serving temperature.
Beat with rotary beater.
Serve hot.

title: cabbage crunch slaw
directions: Toss cabbage, onions and sesame seed.
Combine oil, vinegar, flavoring, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Add dressing, nuts and noodles to cabbage mixture just before serving.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Combine the flour, butter and nuts until crumbly.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam) and bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Cool.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine egg, salt and milk. Add flour. Roll out real thin on a floured surface and then roll up and slice 1/4-inch wide; unroll and spread out to dry for 2 hours.

title: homemade sausages
directions: Mix all ingredients
well
and	roll in 2 or 3 rolls as firmly as	possible.
Place
aluminum foil, shiny side next to meat. Wrap so
seam
side
is up.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours. Punch holes
in bottom of rolls.
Place on rack in pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Chill before slicing.

title: creole sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook, covered, in microwave on High until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Divide into 1/4 cups in paper baking cups.
Freeze.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper to boil.
Mix celery, bell pepper, onions and pimentos.
Drain green beans, corn and peas.
Mix vegetables.
Pour sauce over vegetable mixture. Chill and serve.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: (after church) angel rolls
directions: Combine on Saturday night.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and milk.
Stir into mixture the dissolved yeast, oil and flour.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not peel cucumbers.
Slice.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Add salt and cover with cracker ice and mix thoroughly. Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Do not rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to boiling. Seal in hot jars.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, nuts and frosting mix.
Mix well. Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool 2 hours in pan.
Remove and cool completely before serving.

title: tomato-cucumber salad
directions: Slice tomatoes, cut in half.
Combine tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and parsley in serving dish.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables and toss gently.
Refrigerate at least half hour.
Serves 6.

title: eva's frozen pickles(makes 2 pints)
directions: Cut cucumbers in 1/8-inch thick slices. Place in large bowl with onions, salt and water. Let stand 2 hours, stirring occasionally; drain but do not rinse. Return cucumbers to bowl. Add sugar, vinegar and celery seed. Let stand, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves and covers the cucumbers. Pack in freezer containers. Seal and freeze. When ready to use, thaw and store in refrigerator.

title: pacific salmon pie
directions: Grease 9 inch pie pan with 1 tsp. margarine. Melt remaining margarine in frying pan. Saute onion & celery. Beat 1 egg and pepper into rice. Pour rice into pie plate to form a crust.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook, bone and cut into pieces the chicken.
Drain the peas and carrots and mix together the soups and broth.
Layer the chicken, then peas and carrots; pour soup mixture over chicken and peas; mix together milk and Bisquick and pour over this.
Use a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Heat soup and butter until hot.
Add asparagus.
Layer crumbs, asparagus mixture and cheese.
Repeat.
Heat in microwave until hot.

title: country club pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° to 350° for 30 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Boil pork roast for 2 hours, then put in oven.
Pour barbecue sauce over the roast and cook for 1 hour at 375°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a boil. Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour over other ingredients in a large bowl.
Use electric mixer and mix until all is blended well.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in butter, then arrange in 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Divide dried beef in half and chip.
Mix cream cheese, onions, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 of chipped dried beef.
Form into ball and roll in remainder of dried beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Cook meat and onions separately; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and heat.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan layers of broken tortillas.
Pour half of meat mixture on top and then place another layer of tortillas and then rest of meat; cover.
Cook at 375° for 60 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and chopped onions.
Serve with Spanish rice and refried beans.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Dissolve jello	in hot water;
cool.
Add marshmallows, bananas and pineapple.
Pour
into	9 x 13-inch glass cake pan or large mold.
Place	in refrigerator to set.
Mix 1 1/2 cups pineapple
juice
(add water to make amount), sugar, flour and butter.
Cook
until
thick.
Add eggs and Knox gelatine (dissolve in
a little cold water).	Cool.
Add whipped cream and place on top of set jello.
Cut in pieces and serve.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Brown cut up fryer in butter and shortening until brown.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons shortening.
Add onion, bell pepper, salt to taste, cranberry sauce and water.
Simmer about 45 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in sheet cake pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook and stir until browned.
Add broccoli, red pepper and water chestnuts; cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic powder and ginger; stir into chicken mixture.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Prepare rice as directed on package, omitting margarine and salt.
Serve chicken and vegetables over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Add the first three ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Then take off heat.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Beat with mixer until mixed up.
Butter the pan and then pour.
Let set until hard.

title: peach delight
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Drain peaches and cut into smaller pieces.
Mix peaches, yogurt and Cool Whip together. Place on cooled cake.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and mix in squash, then fold in carrots.
Make Stove Top stuffing.
Mix as directed on box.
Line the bottom of baking dish with half the stuffing mix.
Pour the squash mixture, then add the other half of stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy orzo
directions: Prepare orzo pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in small saucepan, saute onion in margarine for 5 minutes, until translucent.
Stir in flour and salt; cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk and thyme.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Reduce heat to low; stir in Parmesan cheese.
Continue cooking 3 to 4 minutes, until cheese melts.
Stir orzo into cheese sauce.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese curls and thyme sprig.

title: italian chicken
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil until browned.
After browned, remove from pan.
In the same pan with the oil, saute onion, celery and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes with juice, chicken broth, wine, seasonings and the cooked chicken.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
In this time, cook the pasta.
When done, drain and add butter and parsley.
The last 5 minutes of the chicken, add bread crumbs and olives.

title: no bake butter balls(good)
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add water, vanilla and oats.
Blend well.
Chill.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts, colored sugar, chocolate, coconut or cinnamon.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: patio baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and saute over medium heat until crisp. Drain bacon on paper towels, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon drippings until tender (5 minutes).

title: chinese chicken
directions: Boil chicken in
water until tender.
Remove from water and shred all the
meat
from the chicken into a shallow dish. Spread green onion together with the grated ginger on chicken. Add soy sauce to taste (or dash of salt, if you prefer).
Heat oil until hot and pour on top, mixing all the ingredients.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork slowly in shortening.
Add 1 cup water, bouillon cube and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover and simmer until tender; drain pineapple and save syrup.
Add brown sugar, syrup, cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Put into saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add sauce to pork; mix well.
Stir in pineapple chunks, sliced green pepper and thinly sliced onion.
Cook over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender and crisp.

title: linguine with broccoli and tomatoes
directions: Cook pasta according to directions without adding salt. While pasta cooks, slice tomatoes lengthwise in 4 slices and cut in thin strips.
About 3 minutes before pasta is done, add broccoli and cook until broccoli is just tender and pasta is tender, but firm.
Scoop about 1/4 cup pasta water into large bowl. Add the garlic in bowl with water.
Drain pasta and broccoli and transfer to bowl. Add tomatoes, cheese, salt, pepper and olive oil. Toss to combine.
Serves 4.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla and salt.
Stir together cocoa and coloring. Add to butter mixture. Sift the flour with baking powder and add alternately with the milk. Stir the baking soda into the vinegar and fold gently into the batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before frosting with white icing, buttercream style.

title: soft zucchini cookies
directions: Mix the zucchini, soda, sugar and margarine; beat well and add 1 egg.
Then add all the other ingredients to the mixture, mixing well.
You can add nuts, raisins or chocolate chips (1/2 cup) if you desire.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pig-n-taters
directions: Place enough oil in skillet to barely cover bottom of pan. Heat and add pork strips.
Brown on both sides.
Add onion, cilantro, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Pour in 1 glass water. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
I use a big electric skillet.
It seems to hold more.

title: patsy's homemade peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add condensed milk and Pet milk.
Add salt, flavoring and peaches.
Pour in gallon homemade ice cream container.
Add whole milk up to fill line and freeze according to your ice cream freezer directions.

title: corn stick muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
