Place a couple of drops of oil in muffin pan.
Place empty muffin pan in 375-400 degree oven. When muffin pan is hot, spoon mix into pan (should sizzle).
Bake until golden brown. Great with soup, fresh peas, crumpled up in milk or hot with butter.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine pretzels, 3 packages Equal and margarine. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: crispy catfish
directions: Rinse catfish in cold water; pat very dry with paper towels. Mix together the crumbs and seasonings; place in shallow bowl.
Dip each fish in melted butter or margarine, then roll in seasoned crumbs.
Place fish on oiled rack 4 inches above hot coals.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes per side, turning once gently.
Serve immediately.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic until vegetables are tender.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: mounds candy bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on back of box using milk in the place of water in 1 (9 x 13 x 2-inch) baking pan or dish, greased and floured.
While this is cooking, combine sweetened condensed milk and cream of coconut and stir.
As soon as cake comes out of the oven, pour this mixture over the cake, punching holes in the cake to soak up the mixture.
After the cake has cooled, spread whipped topping over the top and sprinkle with the entire bag of coconut.
Refrigerate until you are ready to enjoy.

title: harvard beets
directions: Use 1/2 of liquid in can.
Pour in saucepan.
Mix together vinegar, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil; add beets and butter.
Heat until hot all the way through.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add water and cook until thick. Add jello and coloring and let cool.
Line a baked pastry shell with berries; pour mixture over berries. Put in refrigerator and let congeal. Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 2 deep dish pies.

title: party punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Pour over ice in large bowl.
Fill bowl with lemon-lime soda.
Makes about 50 punch cup servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and beat this; add peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; mix well and add vanilla.
Bake in 400° oven.

title: mary thrash's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all
well.	Put
in casserole. Crumble potato chips on top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form dough into teaspoon size balls.
Press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix cooked chicken breast cubes, soups and vegetables together. Refrigerate overnight.
Prepare crust as directed.
Place chicken, soups and vegetable mixture in the bottom pie crust.
Top with other crust and bake until crust is browned.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Spread in bottom of 8 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cookie or brownie icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until there are no lumps left. Add food coloring, sprinkles, chocolate chips or whatever you desire and frost.
After use, refrigerate.

title: overnight caramel rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place 12 frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch pudding (dry).
(Do not use instant pudding.)
Sprinkle brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Drizzle the warm melted butter over all.
Prepare at bedtime; let rise overnight.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 20 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes; invert on plate.

title: spanish royal
directions: Brown hamburger.
Grate cheese.
Mix soups, water, taco sauce and milk together.
Put in a large pan a layer of chips, meat, onion and cheese.
Pour sauce over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed endive
directions: Prepare wild rice according to directions.
Chill.
Separate endive leaves.
Combine the rice, raisins, pine nuts, mayonnaise, sour cream and curry powder; mix well.
Stuff the endive leaves with the rice mixture.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Open condensed milk and put in bowl. Add 1/2 cup lemon juice and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip until mixed. Put in graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate for about 2 hours or until firm.

title: sweet tomato relish
directions: Cut cucumbers in small slices.
If small, cut lengthwise. Place in strong salt brine that will float an egg.
Let soak for three days.
Then soak in clear water with one level tablespoon alum per one gallon water.
Change water every day for three days. Pour vinegar over pickles to get measurement, then add 1/2 teaspoon alum per 1/2 gallon vinegar.
Bring vinegar, alum and pickles to a boil, then drain.
Keep vinegar mixture.
Measure pickles and use 6 cups sugar per 1 gallon of slices.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar mixture.
Make a spice bag using one tablespoon mixed spices per 1 gallon pickles.
Pour boiling vinegar mixture over slices and let stand several days.
Can cold.

title: mount desert brownies
directions: Sift and set aside flour and baking powder.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar and eggs (1 at a time); add vanilla and flour.
Put in well-oiled 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Do not overcook (23 minutes for fudgier brownies).

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain.
Add cheese, melted butter and seasonings.
Put in small casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat thoroughly in a 350° oven.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine and boil 7 minutes the first 4 ingredients.
Add the last three ingredients.
Beat by hand for 5 minutes.
Drop on wax paper.
Makes a lot.
Very good and rich.

title: old-time beef stew
directions: Heat oil.
Brown beef cubes in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer very slowly for several hours.
Thicken with a mixture of 1/2 water and 1/2 flour.

title: maple-nut cupcakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream the butter; add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Combine water and maple syrup and add alternately with the dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Turn into lined or greased muffin tins and bake in moderate (350°) oven about 20 minutes.

title: grandma kibler's apple butter
directions: Put 10 gallons of cider in a copper-lined iron kettle over a fire outside.
Measure or mark the pot where 10 gallons comes to. This will be the line of the finished apple butter.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans until barely tender. Brown onion and pepper in butter; mix with limas which have been drained.
Heat soup and pour over lima mixture; mix gently.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Grind shrimp, onion and garlic in food chopper.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well with hands. Shape into small balls, then roll in flour and fry until brown. Add balls to gravy.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine the corn with the eggs.
Stir in the flour, baking powder and salt.
If too thin, add more flour.
Mix the batter until smooth.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a greased griddle and fry like pancakes.
Serve with meat or alone with syrup or sorghum.

title: upside-down brownies
directions: Place on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish after combined. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: double fudge brownie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 13x9 inch pan. Combine brownie mix, contents of fudge packet from mix, eggs, water, and oil in large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 stokes.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 18 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over brownie base, then sprinkle with peanut butter chips, pecans, and coconut.
Pour milk over top.
Bake 22-25 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool completely in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: smithfield ham(cooked overnight)
directions: Soak ham overnight; scrub.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place ham in a large covered baking pan, skin side up.
Cover ham with 7 cups water.
Place ham in oven.
Turn oven to 500°.
Cook 10 minutes after oven reaches 500°.
Leave oven off for 3 hours.
Leave ham in oven.
Do not open oven.
Turn oven to 500°.
Cook 15 minutes after temperature is reached.
Leave ham in closed oven for 8 hours.
Do not open oven during entire cooking.

title: cheese filled pears
directions: Drain pears and place side by side in baking dish. Mix cream cheese and honey until smooth. Stuff pear halves with cheese mixture. Sprinkle with wafer crumbs. Bake 350° 15-20 minutes. Great side dish for turkey or ham.

title: fat-free apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring well. Lightly grease tube pan with Pam. Bake 1 hour at 325° or until done. Let cool 5 minutes before turning out onto plate.

title: crab sandwiches
directions: Thaw crabmeat if frozen.
Combine crabmeat, cheese, celery and parsley.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard and liquid hot pepper sauce.
Toss crabmeat mixture with dressing.
Split and toast English muffins; spread muffins with margarine.
Place approximately 1/4 cup crab mixture and top with 1 slice cheese on each half of English muffins.
Broil about 4 inches from source of heat for 4 to 5 minutes, until cheese is melted and crab mixture is heated.
Serves 4.

title: ten dollar pie
directions: Mix
together the sugar, flour, milk and baking powder. Melt the
butter
and
combine
with sugar mixture.
Heat the fruit and
have
some extra sugar on top of it.
Combine with sugar mixture.
Turn into deep dish 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole dish. Add 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm seasoning on top with melted butter mix. Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix onion, crumbs, beef, eggs, salt, curry powder, cheeses, seasoned salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together.
Form into large marble size meatballs.
Roll in flour and brown in shortening.
Drain on paper towel.

title: "in a hurry pizza"
directions: Brown muffins, then top with drops of olive oil, spices, 1 tablespoon of crushed tomatoes, grated cheese, finely diced Mozzarella and thin sliced pepperoni.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Watch carefully so they do not burn.
Enjoy!

title: refrigerator garlic-cheese roll
directions: Sprinkle paprika on wax paper.
Mix ingredients and then roll mixture to the size of a Ritz cracker with your hands.
Roll in paprika until all sides are covered.
Wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.
Slice thin and serve on Ritz crackers.
Makes 2 long rolls.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter.
Add sugar slowly.
Add milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Put in crust and freeze.
Keeps frozen for several months.

title: spinach spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on crackers or bread for fancy sandwiches.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Crush noodles slightly and cook in boiling water for 1 minute. Drain in colander.
In a large bowl, combine noodles, cabbage and onions.

title: vanilla wafer crumb crust
directions: Thoroughly blend crumbs and butter.
Press firmly against bottom and edge of pie plate.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes in a moderately hot (375°) oven.
Cool and fill with your favorite filling.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for about 2 hours.

title: hamburger summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix once each day for 4 days.
On 4th day, make into small rolls, about 5. Place on broiler pan so juices can drain.
Bake at 175° for 8 hours; cool.

title: acorn squash and apple puree
directions: Remove the seeds and strings of the acorn squash; discard. Arrange the squash, cut sides down in a glass dish.
Prick the skin all over with the tip of a sharp knife and microwave the squash at High power (100%) for 10 minutes.
Put the apple in a 1 or 2-cup glass measuring cup.
Cover it with microwave-safe plastic wrap and microwave it and the squash at High power (100%) for 4 to 6 minutes or until they are tender.
Scoop out the squash discarding their skin.
Pour off any liquid from the apple and force the squash and the apple through the medium dish of a food mill into a bowl.
Stir in the butter, the nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.

title: top blade steak with vegetables
directions: Chop potatoes, onions and carrots like for stew.
Wash steaks. Put in a baking pan.
Put potatoes, onions and carrots in same baking pan with steaks.
Pour water in pan with steaks and vegetables.
Sprinkle with black pepper and salt to taste.
Cook until meat is done or until water is almost gone.
Can be baked or cooked on top of stove.
Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Empty jello powder into Cool Whip. Mix all ingredients in bowl and chill. Add pecans or walnuts. For larger amount, use large size of everything.

title: uncle jamie's rice pudding
directions: Use heavy bottom pot to prevent burning.
Mix rice, sugar, milk, vanilla and cinnamon sticks over low heat.
Add orange quarters and heat until rice is fully cooked.
In separate pan mix egg and slowly add a little of rice pudding into the egg and whip well.
Combine all into a big pot and heat for 5 minutes.
Remove orange and cinnamon sticks.
Remove from fire.
Dish and serve (top with ground cinnamon), then eat.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in slow cooker.
Turn heat on medium. Stir often until all blended together.

title: ham rolls
directions: Microwave cream cheese in small bowl (20 seconds).
Stir in lemon juice and onion powder.
Spread cheese mixture on ham slices (thinly).
Roll ham from narrow end.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Slice into quarters.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion together; drain.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, basil and parsley.
Pour in tomato sauce; add a little water.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles according to directions.
Layer in large pan the noodles, sauce and cheese.

title: festive fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, undrained pineapple and mashed bananas.
Pour half the mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour, until firm.
Beat cream cheese with sour cream and sugar; spread over chilled layer. Gently spoon remaining Jell-O mixture on top.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes 12.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cook sauce until thick.
Pour over 5 pounds of chicken wings and marinate for several hours.
Cook in the sauce at 325° for approximately 2 hours.
This can be a dinner meat or served at cocktail or buffet table.

title: brownie cookie
directions: Mix together butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add together with other bowl.
Add nuts to mixture.
Drop teaspoon size balls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to
9 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in a nonstick skillet, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir onion and green pepper into bread crumbs.
Add ground beef and remaining ingredients, mixing well. (Mixture will be soft.)
Shape into a 12-inch loaf and place on a lightly greased rack.
Place rack in a broiler pan.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grasshopper brownies
directions: Following directions to bake brownies.
Set aside to cool.

title: barbecued shrimp hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook marinade over low heat until thickens (coats spoon) about 20 minutes.
Marinate shrimp overnight or all day.
Wrap with 1/2 slice bacon.
Barbecue until bacon is crisp and loses transparency.
Make another recipe of marinade for dip.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Beat whites until stiff; beat yolks and add butter and buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients, then add whites and vanilla. Pour one cup of batter into preheated Belgian waffle cooker.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Cook egg noodles.
Drain.
Mix the tomato soup into the hamburger and place into an oblong casserole pan.
(Keep the soups in their condensed state, do not dilute). Cover the hamburger mixture with the cheese.
Mix the condensed cream of chicken soup into the noodles and place over the hamburger, cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with 1 egg and vegetable oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth; spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: shortbread
directions: Thoroughly blend butter and sugar; combine with flour and cornstarch mixture.
Press into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, until just pale golden in color.
If baked too long, shortbread will be hard.
Score into small pieces while still warm.

title: apple cherry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside. In large bowl, combine cherries and apples.
Add sugar mixture; toss to coat.
Put in 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Dot fruit with margarine.
Add top crust.
Seal and flute edge.
Brush top crust with milk.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Cut slits in the top crust.
Cover edge with foil.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry sugar-free dessert
directions: Put strawberry pie filling on the bottom of a medium sized dish. Slice angel food cake and lay over pie filling.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello as directed on package along with cream cheese. Place in refrigerator.
When nearly congealed, add pineapple and nuts and fold in Cool Whip.

title: no cook vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and put in freezer; freeze.
Can add any kind of fruit.
Adding Oreo cookies makes great chocolate ice cream.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 tablespoon sugar and melted butter until blended.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan; chill. Beat cream cheese with 3/4 cup sugar until well blended.
Beat in pumpkin, spices and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Spread sour cream and 1/4 cup sugar over top.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool and remove sides.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns in refrigerator.
Salt and pepper to taste. Melt margarine and mix everything in large bowl.
Butter a 9 x 13 dish and add all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix thoroughly. Makes two 8 or 9 inch pie crusts.
Bake pie shell at 450° for eight minutes.

title: golden salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar, pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Preheat oven to
Mix
together
sour
cream
and cooked rice.
If the
mixture
seems a little dry, add a small amount of milk.
Spread
a layer of this combination in casserole dish, add cheese
cubes
and strips of jalapeno peppers. Add balance of rice and
top
with
grated
cheese.
Dot with butter.
Cook in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain, then cover with 12 cups of water and 3/4 teaspoon of salt.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat with lid on.
Saute bacon in a skillet for 5 minutes, then add onions and saute for 5 minutes more while stirring often. Remove bacon and onions with slotted spoon and add to the pot, discarding the grease.

Cook for 1 hour or until beans are done, then add parsley, basil, pepper, garlic, bay leaf, olive oil and the remaining salt to the pot along with the potatoes, carrots, cabbage, tomatoes and beef broth.
Cook for 20 minutes more, then add celery and macaroni.
Cook for 30 minutes; remove bay leaf. Serve soup with Parmesan cheese and Italian bread.

title: moose mix
directions: In small bowl beat cream until almost stiff; add 1/2 box instant pudding (your choice of flavor) and add a small amount of milk so mixture does not get real thick.
Continue beating until firm and spread on cake or pie.

title: play it again pasta(day 1)
directions: Brown sausage in Dutch oven; drain on paper towel.
Set aside. Cook mushrooms and garlic in olive oil in Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add sausage, greens, Italian seasonings and tomatoes.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add pasta and toss well.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 8 servings (16 cups).

title: green chili
directions: Fry sausage, beef or pork in a skillet. Add onions and seasonings until done.
Add green chilies, shredded, then add tomatoes and simmer 1/2 hour or until chilies are tender. Serve on beans, eggs or eat as is with tortillas.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in large skillet; drain. Add Spanish rice, corn, beans and tomato sauce. Let mixture heat over medium heat thoroughly. When heated through, put cheese on top and let melt. Serve with pan of cornbread.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Take 1 slice of ham and spread with cream cheese.
Place a green onion at the edge and roll up.
Repeat with each slice of ham.
Refrigerate logs until ready to serve.
Slice logs in 1/2-inch slices.
May use a toothpick to hold, if desired.

title: scalloped deviled ham
directions: Trim crusts from bread; spread slices with deviled ham. Arrange in greased 10 x 6 x 1-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick. Dip slices in egg mixture, then into bread crumbs. Grease cookie sheet with olive oil. Arrange eggplant in single layer on sheet and drizzle with oil. Bake 15 minutes on each side. Set aside.

title: bran yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.
In separate large bowl, combine
shortening,
sugar, bran and salt.
Add boiling water and mix until shortening melts.
Add 1/2 cup whole wheat flour and mix.
Add egg and mix.
Add yeast mixture (yeast dissolved in water)
and
mix.
Add
cup whole wheat flour and mix. Add unbleached flour (1 cup at a time) and mix.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and slice 3/4-inch thick.
Beat egg with salt and pepper.
Dip eggplant in egg and then in potato flakes.
Place in pan that has been coated with margarine.
Pour rest of margarine over top.
Bake at 450° for about 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
When mixture is crumbly, add nuts.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: saucy chicken-mushroom bake
directions: Mix rice and carrots in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In bowl, blend soup mix, mushroom soup and water; pour 1/3 of this over rice. Arrange chicken, meaty side up.
Scatter sliced mushrooms around chicken.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken and mushrooms. Cover; bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, until chicken is fully cooked and rice is tender.

title: maple nut bars
directions: Beat eggs gradually.
Add sugar and then add oil.
Mix well. Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and maple flavoring.
Bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar and cut into bars.

title: fudge cake
directions: Place all ingredients, except chocolate, butter and hot water, in large mixing bowl.
Place chocolate, butter and hot water in pan and heat (low) on top of stove (add water after chocolate and butter have melted; this will thicken).
Add to first mixture in bowl.
Beat all a few minutes until blended.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan in 350° oven for approximately 55 minutes.
Test with broomstick.
Everyone loves this!

title: carole's punch
directions: Brew tea as you normally do to make 1/2 gallon.
In a clean plastic jug pour tea and add pineapple juice.
Put frozen orange juice, sugar and about 1/2 cup of the tea/pineapple juice mixture into a small pan and heat it to dissolve the sugar and the orange juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into gallon jug with the tea and pineapple mixture.
If one gallon container is not full add enough water to fill and mix thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator or freezer to get very cold, almost to a slush.
Pour over crushed ice in a punch bowl.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together at medium speed.
Bake in 3 cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Strawberry Frosting.

title: blackberry bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine eggs, milk and oil; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Spray loaf pan with vegetable spray.
Dump into loaf pan.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes or until golden.

title: twisted strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare pudding mixes according to directions. Drizzle orange juice over cake, then toss to coat. Place half of the cake cubes in deep glass bowl, coat with layers of half each of the pudding mixture, strawberries and grated chocolate. Top with layers of remaining cake cubes, pudding, strawberries and chocolate. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and bell pepper.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Pour over Doritos chips. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn and bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse all the canned vegetables.
Stir in all the ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Will keep up to 10 days in refrigerator.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.

title: meatballs
directions: Roll hamburger mixture in balls and brown in oven for about 20 minutes on 350°.
Drain well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and soups together and pour into lightly buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: curry glaze chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour and ginger that have been mixed. Place in baking dish in melted butter and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Mix remaining ingredients together and boil for 15 or 20 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake 20 to 30 minutes in 400° oven until chicken is completely done.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers and mix melted butter with crackers.
Set aside. In a different dish, mix pudding with milk; then add 1 quart of ice cream and mix.
Put cracker crumbs in bottom of cake pan (saving out 1/2 cup for topping).
Pour pudding mixture on top of crumbs. Top pudding mixture with Cool Whip and sprinkle crumbs on Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.
Do not freeze.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Combine flour, pepper and salt in jar; shake until well combined.
Stir into drippings/oil in skillet.
Stir in liquid; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Add cut up tomato.
Cook and stir another 2 minutes.
If necessary, may be thinned with additional liquid.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine oil and sugar.
Sift half dry ingredients into sugar mixture; blend.
Sift remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and mix well.
Add pecans.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak in serving sizes. Season, flour and brown the steak. Put the steak into a baking pan with chopped onion, tomato sauce and 3 cans of water. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: creamy green enchiladas
directions: Mix beef and salt; brown in skillet. Drain and add Cheddar cheese and onion. Set aside.
Mix soup, milk and Velveeta in saucepan.

Place on low heat, stirring until Velveeta melts. Add dip mix, chilies and pimentos; set aside. Dip tortillas in hot oil for about 1 second to soften; drain well. Spread each tortilla with meat mixture.
Roll tightly and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over tortillas. Cover with foil. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 12.

title: butterhorn cookies
directions: Measure into a bowl the flour and butter.
Cut butter into flour with fingertips.
Then add 1 egg yolk and sour cream.
Mix well.
When blended, shape into a ball, sprinkle with flour and wrap well in waxed paper and chill for a few hours.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle board with flour, lightly. Remove dough from waxed paper and divide into 3 parts. Roll out on board, one section at a time.
Make large circle 1/8-inch thick. Sprinkle with 1/3 mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Cut into 4ths.
Then cut each 4th into 4 wedge shaped pieces.
Roll each wedge, starting from the outside portion toward the center.
Place rolls on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in a moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Moderate oven can be from 350° to 375°.

title: joy's bread
directions: Melt oleo. Mix with biscuit mix and sour cream. Bake in muffin pan at 425° until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 12.

title: never fail beef roast
directions: Wash and prepare beef.
Place in foil in pan.
Mix French onion soup and mushroom soup.
Add to beef roast.
Coat top of roast with dry soup mix.
Completely cover with foil and seal. Bake at 325° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix in order the sour cream, Cool Whip and pudding. Then add crushed pineapple, mini marshmallows, maraschino cherries and chopped nuts.
Chill. Keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: rice cream pie
directions: Measure corn syrup and peanut butter into large bowl; stir until thoroughly combined.
Add Rice Krispies; mix until well-coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly in bottom and around sides of buttered 9-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Spread ice cream evenly in pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Top with golden peach slices or other fresh fruit or syrups.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: lo-cal sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Add Equal, celery, green peppers, onions and vinegar.
Mix together.
The longer you marinate the better. Good over hot dogs or as a salad.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in large skillet.
Drain off fat. While browning hamburg, cook macaroni according to directions on package in large saucepan.
When both are done, combine in large skillet with the tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Let simmer 30 minutes and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, then add nuts and dry ingredients just until blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased, floured pans. Remove from pans to prevent sticking.
Cool on racks.
Makes 2 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: favorite bean soup
directions: Rinse and soak beans overnight.
Add bay leaf, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer for several hours or until beans are tender.
Saute onions and green pepper and add tomatoes.
Allow to cook several minutes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Drain squash. Add onion, soup, carrots, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Butter casserole and
sprinkle layer of crumbs in bottom. Add squash mixture. Cover with crumbs and generous dots of butter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix pumpkin, milk, brown sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients mixture a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gently stir in blueberries last.
Grease or spray muffin pan(s).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Moisten potatoes and shake a few at a time, coating well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in a single layer in pan.
Bake in 375° oven about 1 hour, turning once during baking.
When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix everything together at medium speed with electric mixer.
Chill before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add shortening and mix. Soften with milk. Roll onto floured surface. Cut with round cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet 1 to 2-inches apart. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: barbecue beans bake
directions: Mix beans, bacon, sugar, margarine, cinnamon, barbecue sauce, mustard and black molasses.
Cook in microwave or oven; 30 minutes in oven and 20 minutes in microwave.

title: get together cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cabbage, celery, water, carrot and salt into large saucepan.
Cover and boil 5 minutes; drain well. In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, soy sauce, onion and pepper sauce.
Add drained cabbage; mix well.
Melt butter in small pan.
Add crumbs (can use cornflakes) and mix well. Sprinkle over cabbage.
Bake 40 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: canoe crab dip
directions: Hollow out one loaf of bread.
Break or cut the part you have removed and the entire second loaf into bite-size pieces.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese, crab and onions in baking dish.
May be done ahead to this point and refrigerated.
Bake until hot (350° for 20 to 30 minutes) and pour into hollowed out bread.
Serve surrounded with bread pieces for dipping.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and fold into noodles.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can add cheese and top with bread crumbs, if desired.

title: dip dogs
directions: Put hot dogs in boiling water, and let stand for 5 minutes. Drain and wipe dry.
The hot dogs must stand in the water to get rid of the grease.
Mix dry ingredients in a shallow bowl, and then add the eggs and milk.
Mix well with a fork.
Heat cooking oil to deep fry (about 360°).
Coat each hot dog with the batter and fry until brown on all edges.
The batter will cling well to the hot dogs.

title: low calorie chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle each with dry milk, seasonings and lemon juice. Wrap and bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until tender.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Cream shortening, add sugar, salt and unbeaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add sour cream and dry ingredients alternately.
Add vanilla; chill. Roll thin.
Cut with floured cutter and place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar, roll lightly.
Bake in moderate oven. Remove from cookie sheet at once.
Temperature:
Time:
10 to 12 minutes.
Quantity:
6 dozen medium.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix coconut and pecans together; put in bottom of baking pan.
Make cake mix according to directions on package.
Pour over pecans and coconut. Mix the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar together until creamy. Drop by spoonfuls over the top of the cake batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 32 to 35 minutes or until cake is done. Refrigerate after cake has thoroughly cooled.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green peppers; then add sour cream, tomatoes, sugar and macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: rich and charlie's salad
directions: Chop all items and toss in salad bowl.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Break spaghetti and cook as directed on package.
In a large bowl, beat eggs lightly; stir in milk, 1 cup cheese, garlic powder and salt.
Add cooked spaghetti and stir until combined.
Grease 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
Spread evenly with spaghetti mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread sauce evenly over spaghetti.
Sprinkle oregano and 3 cups cheese over top, then top with pepperoni and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: deluxe lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and salt in a large heavy saucepan; mix well.
Gradually add water and lemon juice, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; gradually stir into lemon mixture.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon rind.
Pour into pastry shell.
Combine egg whites (at room temperature) and cream of tartar; beat until foamy.
Gradually add remaining sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks. Beat in vanilla.
Spread meringue over filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool to room temperature.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand covered 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
You can refrigerate overnight to cook next day or bake immediately at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip-pecan cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed electric mixer.
Beat egg into cream mixture.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and mixture into cream mixture until just blended.
Stir chocolate chips and pecan mixes.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes. Remove to foil on counter.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet at 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir.
With wire whip, blend in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted 1-inch from the edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: fried biscuits
directions: Heat oil to approximately 350°.
Separate biscuits and drop into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning frequently.
Place on paper towel lined plate.
Serve with apple butter.

title: spice bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients all together and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs 1 at a time and beat thoroughly.
Add syrup and honey; mix well.
Add 1/2 of flour and mix until moist enough to add remaining flour and raisins.
Bake at 350° until soft brown.
When mixed, make a ball of dough to roll the length of cookie sheet.
Roll to 1 inch roll; put 2 rolls to a cookie sheet.
Flatten each roll before baking.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine as per package.
Combine garlic and butter and saute.
Add clams, basil, oregano, salt and pepper to garlic and butter mixture.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour over hot linguine.
Add parsley and toss gently.
Place on a warm platter and top with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all
together and bake at 325° until done, at least 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: In large pan, take lasagna noodles and spread with Ricotta and cottage cheese mixture. Put a piece of Mozzarella cheese and then a piece of Swiss cheese. Roll up the lasagna noodle with cheese mixture. Lay rolled up lasagna noodles in pan. When pan is full with rolled up noodles, pour ground beef and tomato mixture. Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or browned. Top with Parmesan cheese. You may also cook in single serving pan also.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and toss altogether.

title: barbecue sausage bites
directions: In a 3 quart slow cooker, combine the sausages.

title: cajun grilled chicken taco
directions: Arrange corn tortilla shells in a sombrero lined with colorful napkins.
Place chicken and toppings to the side for a build-your-own Mexican fiesta feast.

title: pineapple "spoon bread"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Beat in eggs.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour into casserole.

title: sweetheart cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugar and salt until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour and vanilla; stir in cereal.
Shape into balls; indent centers with finger.
Fill centers with preserves.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, celery, olives and green pepper in butter.
Add turkey and remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Spoon a small amount of sauce into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 8 ounces uncooked noodles.
Cover with remaining sauce and top with 8 ounces grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: no bake cashew balls
directions: In large saucepan, place chocolate and butterscotch chips. Stir over low heat until melted. Add 1 3/4 cups finely crushed noodles, powdered sugar, sour cream, orange rind and salt; stir until well blended. Cover; refrigerate 20 minutes. Combine remaining noodles and cashews. Shape chocolate mixture into 1-inch balls; roll in a crushed cashew mixture. Refrigerate until firm. Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute carrots, green peppers, onions and celery in oil until tender.
Stir in meat, cooking until tender.
Add eggs to vegetables and meat mixture, then combine with rice.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper and soy sauce to taste.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together. Sift flour, salt and baking powder three times. Add bananas and vanilla to creamed mixture. Add flour with part of the buttermilk. Stir soda into remaining buttermilk. Then VERY QUICKLY, add to the mixture. Beat 2 eggs and 2 yolks. Add to the mixture. Beat mixture well. Pour into two 8-inch round cake pans. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt. Cook for 4 minutes on High.
Stir and cook 4 minutes longer. Stir in margarine and vanilla; cook 2 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir until foamy, then quickly pour onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Keep in airtight container.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces in large mixing bowl.
Pour entire bottle of dressing over broccoli and cauliflower.
Add poppy seed.
Mix well.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.

title: orange jello salad
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, dissolve Jell-O, sugar and fruit over low heat.
Chill until almost thick.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese; mix well.
Can be made ahead of time and will keep several days.

title: sunny holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve in a punch bowl and garnish with mint leaves.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Stir the flour into this mixture until it forms a soft ball.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll out between waxed paper.
It makes a top and bottom or 2 singles.

title: pig eatin cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed.
Add mandarin oranges. Beat until oranges are well mixed.
Bake in a 3 x 9-inch round pan at 350° until golden.

title: beef jerky
directions: Marinate four to six hours or overnight in glass dish.
Use gas stove on pilot light or dehydrator until completely dry. Store in airtight container.
Lasts for months.
Wonderful for a snack on camping trips.

title: minted peas
directions: Cook peas in boiling water with salt, sugar and mint, about 10 minutes or until peas are tender.
Drain.
Combine butter and lemon juice, pour over peas.
Makes 6 servings.

title: curried chicken
directions: Heat oil; saute slightly the onion.
Add pears; continue sauteing until half cooked.
Add curry powder; mix well.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add soup which has been mixed with milk.
Heat through; add chicken pieces.
Add raisins and nuts; heat well. Serve over brown rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jeff's favorite chuckwagon beans
directions: Pour beans into large Pyrex dish.
Add remaining ingredients except for bacon slices and stir until mixed thoroughly.
Place 3 to 4 bacon slices on top and bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets; wash and drain.
Place broccoli and bacon pieces into large bowl; add shredded cheese.
Chop onion and add to bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; add to broccoli mixture.
Blend and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Cream cheese and sugar together; add eggs and vanilla.	Use midget cupcake papers.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup. Add 1/2 to 3/4 mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: french toast
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add just enough flour to make a thin batter.
Dip slices of bread in batter and fry in oil.
Serve hot with syrup or jam.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Spoon pie filling into glass 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Melt butter in a small glass bowl in microwave (45 to 60 seconds).
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl.
Add melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave 10 to 15 minutes on High. Rotate dish one quarter turn once.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans.
Press evenly into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Layer sliced bananas over cooled crust.
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over bananas.
Combine puddings and milk, after thickened, pour over other layers.
Next layer is well drained pineapple.
Lastly cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Keeps for several days in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground meat.
Boil spaghetti.
Add seasoned salt, sugar, Prego sauce and mustard.
Stir it good and cook for 30 minutes on low heat.

title: oyster cracker munchies
directions: Add all but oil in grocery bag and shake.
Pour in oil and shake real good.
Put sack on newspaper and every 10 minutes, shake again.
Do so for 1 hour.
Put in airtight container.

title: fresh rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix rhubarb, flour, sugar and butter together and place in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together until crumbly. Place on top of rhubarb mixture and shake down through the mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons grease.
Mix all other ingredients well and add to grease.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour over lettuce.
Serve immediately.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 1 stick butter.
Pat in 8 x 12-inch pan for crust.
Mix eggs, confectioners sugar and 1 stick of butter at room temperature; beat 20 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Drain 1 (No. 2) can of crushed pineapple.
Spread over mixture.
Add bananas. Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the last 2.
Lastly add the butter and blueberries. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and heat to boiling. Cool to room temperature.
Chill, covered several hours before serving.
If some sweetness is desired, add some artificial sweetener.
Serves 4.

title: walnut broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Place in oiled casserole. Melt 2 tablespoons margarine. Stir in flour. Add milk and broth. Stir until thick. Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in water. Mix with stuffing and walnuts. Pour broth over broccoli. Sprinkle with stuffing. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Toss all ingredients with Miracle Whip salad dressing.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
If not 1/4 cup fat left in skillet, add oil to make 1/4 cup.
Add celery and onion.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add sugar, vinegar and water all at once and bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring with a whisk.
Add parsley, celery seed and bacon.
Remove from heat.
Place potatoes in oiled 13 x 9-inch pan and pour dressing over all. Mix very gently.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, pour in all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour in floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick tuna and veggie casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a microwavable dish.
Mix well. Microwave on High 16 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: seafood appetizer
directions: Wrap with 1/3 slice bacon.
Put small pat of butter, dash of Tabasco and dash of paprika (a little chopped onion or jalapeno, if desired).
Wrap all with bacon and fasten with toothpick to hold together.
Broil.
When bacon is done, it's ready to serve.

title: springtime noodles(tagliarini primavera)
directions: Cut asparagus diagonally into 1 inch lengths, but leave tips whole.
In a wide frying pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add mushrooms, ham, asparagus, carrot and zucchini, and cook, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes.
Cover pan and cook 1 more minute. Meanwhile, cook noodles in a large kettle of boiling salted water until al dente; drain well.
To vegetable mixture add green onions, peas, basil, salt, nutmeg, pepper and cream.
Increase heat to high and cook until liquid boils well and forms large shiny bubbles.
Return drained noodles to kettle in which they were cooked.
Pour the vegetable mixture over the noodles and lift and mix gently until noodles are thoroughly coated.
Add the Parmesan cheese and mix again.
Turn into a warm bowl and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve at once with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: peach crumb pie
directions: In bowl, stir together flour and sugar.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until crumbs form.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, mix cornstarch and ginger.
Stir in corn syrup until smooth.
Add peaches.
Toss to coat.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and pumpkin.
Add egg; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice while cookies are warm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into flat glass dish that is sprayed with Pam.
Put 1 cup of crushed crackers and 1/2 cup of butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: granny's meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: avocado dressing
directions: Combine dairy sour cream, milk, lemon juice, celery salt and a few dashes of bottled hot pepper sauce.
Stir in avocado, seeded, peeled and mashed.
If necessary, stir in additional milk to achieve desired serving consistency.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add eggs.
Beat together.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add 1 can evaporated milk and mix all together.
Sprinkle 1/2 coconut in bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Add 1/2 cup pecans; pour 1/2 pie mixture over coconut and pecans.
Bake at 400° until pie is consistency of custard and a golden brown.
Repeat with second pie crust and rest of ingredients.
Makes 2 pies.

title: quick skillet macaroni
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Add macaroni; mix well.
Bring mixture to boil.
Then reduce heat to low simmer, uncover 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until macaroni is tender. Garnish with minced parsley if desired.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup with milk and mayo.
Layer chicken and broccoli cubes and 1/2 onions.
Pour mixture over all.
Top with fried onions and cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through (25 to 35 minutes).

title: green beans deluxe
directions: Cook the onion for 10 minutes in the liquid from the beans. Add the beans and heat thoroughly.
Just before serving, stir in the water chestnuts.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: bakeless fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in double boiler with Pet milk.
Then mix all together.
Press in loaf pans lined with wax paper.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and bread crumbs.
Put in a casserole dish that is lightly greased.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: original green bean casserole
directions: Drain juice if using canned beans.
Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for five minutes or until onions are golden.
Serves 6.

title: mother's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix with beater or by hand in a large dish.
Put in ice cream freezer and finish filling with milk.
Don't overfill.
Put can in tub, then fill with 3 inches of ice.
Add rock salt, then more ice, until filled.
When time is up, take dasher out and pack with ice.

title: date pie
directions: Roll crackers fine.
Add chopped nuts, chopped dates and sugar.
Mix well with cracker crumbs.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pat in a well-buttered pie dish (no crust).

title: mustard pickles
directions: Put all dry ingredients in jars where cucumbers have been packed.
Mix vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Place quart jars in a hot water bath canner; bring to a rolling boil; turn off immediately and let set in canner for a few minutes.
Remove jars from canner.
Be sure the jars seal.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cook 1/2 cup milk, brown sugar and chocolate.
Stir carefully to keep from sticking.
Cool.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and 1/2 cup milk and combine with flour (sifted 3 times with baking soda added) alternately while adding to first mixture and bake in 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: In large saucepan, bring water to a boil, adding the garlic, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in the grits.
Lower the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the butter and 1 cup Cheddar cheese until the butter melts.
Mix the eggs with milk and stir thoroughly into the grits.
Turn the grits into a greased 2-quart round casserole. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven 1 hour or until set and browned.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Combine melted butter and crushed vanilla wafers to make crust.
Press into pan.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, salt, vanilla, flour and heavy cream.
Add 4 beaten egg yolks.
Stiffen egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour onto crust.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until you see a crack in the cheesecake. Top with cherries, blueberries, strawberries, etc.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Shape into balls; roll in coconut (optional) or pat flat in a pan as fudge.
Refrigerate if not eaten right away.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Place round steak in freezer until just partially frozen. Remove and cut in long and very thin slices. Melt 2 tablespoons butter together with olive oil in heavy skillet. Cook strips of steak over medium heat until done.

Place meat on heated serving platter; set aside. Melt rest of butter in skillet and saute onion until transparent. Add mushrooms and continue just until heated through. Add wine and cook 2 to 3 minutes until alcohol evaporates. Add sour cream, chili sauce and salt and pepper to taste. Stir frequently; bring to boiling point. Do not boil. Pour over meat. Serve with buttered noodles.

title: cream chez bars
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: taco salad(diabetic recipe)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain away fat.
Add spices, beans and tomato and heat.
Top 1 cup lettuce with 1 cup meat mixture.
Spoon 2 tablespoons salsa sauce and 1 tablespoon sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving equals 1 1/2 bread and 2 meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Mix and spread fudge in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Freeze for 1 hour and store in refrigerator.

title: liver pate
directions: Line a 1-pint mold with some of the bacon.
Set in refrigerator.
Cut remaining bacon into small pieces and cook 5 minutes with onion and parsley.
Add liver and cook until brown, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Combine milk and bread crumbs in a bowl and let stand.
When liver is cooled, puree liver and stir in egg yolk.
Drain excess liquid from bread crumbs and reserve.
Add moistened crumbs to liver mixture.
Season with spices.
Add enough reserved milk to make a thick paste that will drop from a spoon.
Pack into the mold.
Cover and set in a pan of hot water. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Cool; turn out onto a serving dish. Serve with plain crackers.

title: doc's corn bread
directions: Mix thoroughly the corn meal, biscuit flour, salt, creamed corn, baking powder and eggs.
Add butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Whip gently.
Pour into buttered pans.
Bake at 400°.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Butter baking pan, spread cherry filling over the bottom of pan.
Top with pineapple.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Dribble melted
margarine
evenly over cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and blend thoroughly. Let chill in refrigerator until able to roll into ball. Roll in chopped pecans. Serve with any saltines or variety crackers. A great appetizer for parties or the holidays!

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and egg yolks; beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Add vanilla and 1/2 of the flour; beat 2 minutes.
Pour in milk and beat another minute.
Add remaining flour and baking powder and mix 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° until firm and springy to the touch.

title: "irish stew" - steak soup(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Add more potatoes, if needed.
Add all ingredients to water mixture.
Bring to boil and then simmer for 1 or 2 hours.

title: taco el grande
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Add spices and tomatoes.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Layer 1/2 meat mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a layer of rice on top.
Add a layer of meat again.
Heat soup with the milk and pour over mixture.
Sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Fritos, chopped tomatoes, onions, lettuce and sour cream.

title: quick pecan pie
directions: Gradually add sugar and salt to egg whites.
Fold in crumbs and nuts.
Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter, bacon and onion spread
directions: Fry bacon until crispy; drain on paper towel.
Crumble.
In a small bowl combine the peanut butter with the bacon and onion; blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: mini cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
In bottom of foil muffin liners, place a vanilla wafer (flat side down); fill about 1/2 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until set, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown.
Mix together sour cream and 3/4 cup sugar.
Drop spoonful on top of each cheese cake and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Keep in fridge.
When ready to serve, top with cherry pie filling.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and sterilize two 1/2-gallon jars.
Slice cucumbers and onions in layers into jars; pack well.
(Use whatever it will hold.)
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices; do not heat.
Stir well and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate for at least 5 days before using.
Keep refrigerated at all times.
Good for 1 year.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour custard into pastry shell.
Bake 10 minutes; reduce temperature to 300° and continue baking until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and chocolate.
Pour into a greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 3/4-inch pan (about).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
48 squares.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: *I substitute turmeric for saffron.

title: lee fennel's potato soup
directions: In saucepan, boil potatoes in just enough water to cover plus salt and pepper.
In another large pot, melt the butter and cook onion, then stir in flour.
Mix well.
Add milk and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add cooked potatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve. Increase cheese if you like it thicker.

title: brandied fruit
directions: The fruit needs 2 weeks to ferment after you start the first batch or after you feed it, but you can let a batch set at room temperature for weeks and still use it.
As it sets and ferments without feeding, the brandy taste will become stronger, but it keeps indefinitely.
If a batch tastes too strong after several weeks, feed it with more fruit and sugar and let it ferment for 2 weeks.
It will then be ready to use.
A glass container allows you to watch the process and is sure to turn into a conversation piece.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop lettuce and break cauliflower into bite-sized pieces. Then layer in large bowl in the following order: Lettuce, cauliflower, mayonnaise (spread over top), sugar (sprinkled evenly), Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Chill thoroughly and stir just before serving.

title: edi's hush puppies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Dip spoon in 1 cup of medium hot water before each spoonful of mixture is dropped into hot oil. Fry in hot oil until each rises to the top.

title: roast beef in a crock-pot
directions: Put roast in crock-pot.
Add water. Add potatoes and carrots. Sprinkle on onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper (as much as you like). Turn crock-pot on high for at least 6 hours or until done.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples in crust; sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Work together oleo, flour and 1/2 cup sugar. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: wassail(beverage)
directions: Steep for 1 hour.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut angel food cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the dry cake mix, pineapple and coconut extract. Beat on low speed for 30 seconds; beat on medium for 1 minute. Pour into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Immediately invert pan; cool completely. Carefully run a knife around sides of pan. Remove cake to a serving plate.

title: paprikas
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Cover with paprika.
Place in large pot with bouillon cubes and just enough water to boil gently.
Salt and pepper beans, cover with paprika and add to pot. Salt and pepper potatoes, cover with paprika and add to pot. Boil gently until chicken and vegetables are done.
Remove from liquid and set aside.
Add sour cream to liquid and simmer until slightly thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables and heat slowly.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts mixed together.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
(No need to frost!
All in pan before baking.)

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water; let stand for 10 minutes.
Cream melted margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Add this mixture to yeast water.
Add flour; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Easy and delicious!

title: mexican hamburger-corn bread bake
directions: Dump all ingredients into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In order as they are written, layer the ingredients in a large salad bowl:
lettuce, peas, broccoli, green peppers, onions, carrots, cheese, bacon bits and top with a thick layer of mayonnaise.
Garnish with remainder of cheese and bacon bits. Refrigerate for at least one hour before serving, overnight is best.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and mix gently. Combine pudding mix and reserved pineapple juice in mixing bowl. Beat until thick.
Pour over fruit; toss gently. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add milk, crushed pineapple and bread cubes.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: summer cake
directions: Bake cake (according to instructions on box) in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Blend together pudding and cream cheese.
Spread on top of cake.
On top of that spread a layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle nuts and pineapple over all.

title: tahisian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add boiling water and stir to mix.
Let stand.
Soak yeast cakes in lukewarm water, then add to sugar mixture.
Stir in salt, eggs and flour until well mixed.
Mix thoroughly until forms a ball and cleans the dish. Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Take out about 1 1/2 hours before ready to serve.
Make up rolls and put in greased muffin pans and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Over this Pour 1 1/2 c. hot water.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Simmer corned beef approximately 1 hour per lb.
Add vegetables to kettle 40 minutes before meat is done.

title: esther's chocolate fudge
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, heat the sugar, milk, corn syrup, salt and chocolate (or cocoa) to boiling, stirring frequently.
Carefully set candy thermometer in place and cook, without stirring, until temperature reaches 238° or soft ball stage.
This takes about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool mixture, without stirring, to 110° or until outside of saucepan is lukewarm.
When mixture is cool, beat with a wooden spoon until mixture becomes thick and begins to lose its gloss.
Quickly stir in the nuts and pour fudge into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
(Do not scrape saucepan as mixture on sides may contain sugar crystals.) Cool pan on a wire rack.
Cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.

title: creamy apple pie
directions: Beat first three ingredients well with mixer.
Gradually add flour until mixture forms soft dough.
Press into bottom and up sides of deep 9-inch pie pan.

title: apple chunk cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put it in an 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Pour in milk and heat to lukewarm.
Add egg yolks (beaten), vanilla flavoring and butter. Stir until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Add meringue.

title: migas ranchero
directions: Cut tortillas in 1-inch cubes and brown in enough oil to coat until tortillas are crispy.
Add chopped purple onions and bell pepper.
Brown until onions are clear.
Add eggs.
Cook until done. Lower heat and add cheese and jalapeno pepper.
Remove from heat and serve with salsa.

title: juanice's blueberry pie
directions: Pour berries into crust.
Cut butter up and place on top of berries.
Mix up sugar, flour and eggs.
Pour over the top of berries and butter pats.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: hot and spicy pickles
directions: In bottom of jar, place dill sprig, hot peppers and garlic, sliced thin (2 to 3 toes).
Pack jar firmly with cucumbers.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a rolling boil.
Turn down to simmer 5 to 7 minutes, then pour into jars.
Seal.
Yields 5 to 7 pints.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Combine beef, onion and macaroni in large pot.
Add seasonings and tomatoes; heat to simmering. Sprinkle soda over top; stir until mixture foams.
Add enough milk to make it thick and soupy.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: julie's zucchini muffins
directions: Mix flour with sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda until blended.
Set aside 1/2 cup nuts.
Combine remaining nuts with raisins and set aside.
Add zucchini to flour mixture.
Blend eggs.
Add to flour mixture. Stir until moistened and add raisin/nut mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes for bread and 25 minutes for muffins.

title: prize winning shish kabobs
directions: Marinate cubes of lamb, beef or chicken overnight or for several hours in sauce made by combining all ingredients.
When ready to cook, thread meat on skewers alternating a vegetable such as potato (partially cooked), onion, green pepper, mushrooms or carrots (partially cooked).

title: granny's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sprinkle a little sugar over yeast.
Combine scalded milk, sugar, oil, and salt.
Add to lukewarm milk mixture and combine.
Add flour gradually until it gets too thick to mix with beater.
Turn on to well-floured surface; continue to knead (about 5 minutes).
Form into round ball and place in well-oiled bowl and cover; allow to rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and knead 2 to 3 times.
Form into rolls, and allow to rise again until they have doubled in size. Bake at 400 degrees until they are golden brown.

title: cranberry butter
directions: Whip the butter and margarine until smooth. Add honey and sugar. Add cranberries and nuts. Whip until smooth. Add red food coloring if not dark enough.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut onion into one-fourth-inch slices.
Beat eggs well and add milk.
Sift flour and measure.
Sift dry ingredients together in bowl.
Gradually add the liquid and beat until smooth.
Add melted butter.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Heat broth in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry garlic, onion and chicken for 10 minutes (drain off some liquid if more than 1/4 cup juices is collected).
Add pepper and seasonings and stir-fry additional 8 minutes. Stir in salsa and lime juice. Heat thoroughly another 2 or 3 minutes and serve immediately.

title: pasta and peas
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes and oregano; cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Boil pasta al dente; drain and add peas.
Pour sauce over pasta and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: fresh mint bridal tea
directions: Put the sugar in a saucepan and just cover with some water. Bring this to a boil stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in fresh mint.
Set aside to cool.
Brew tea with the remaing water.
Cool.

title: aunt jan's potato pot
directions: Combine, dot with butter and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until heated.

title: korean beef
directions: Marinate the beef overnight.
Grill the beef until tender and brown.
You may substitute chicken breasts.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together eggs, butter and confectioners sugar until well blended.
Spread over cracker crumbs.
Add crushed pineapple (drained well) and bananas over mixture.
Spread Cool Whip and garnish with pecans and cherries. Leave in refrigerator overnight or 8 hours.

title: german pancakes
directions: Mix eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan while oven is preheating.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Don't peek before 12 minutes!
This will rise like a souffle.
This is ample for two.
Serve with syrup.

title: venison stew
directions: Heat the fresh bacon drippings in a Dutch oven.
Slice onions and saute until brown on all sides.
Then add fried onions and rest of ingredients.
Cover and cook over slow heat for 3 1/2 hours.
If stew gets too thick, add more beef broth.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; add mushrooms, tomato soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Boil egg noodles; drain and combine with meat mixture.
Put all in casserole with grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Pare, clean and cut eggplant into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Salt the slices and let stand for about an hour.
Squeeze out water from salted eggplant.
Dip eggplant first in flour, then beaten egg, then into bread crumbs.
Let stand about 1/2 hour, then fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Butter a baking dish or a casserole, then layer eggplant, then tomato sauce, eggplant, etc., until eggplant is used.
Top with grated cheese and bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: basic cookie dough(soft sugar)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder, then vanilla.
To this you may add anything you like in cookies - raisins, nuts, fruits, chips (any kind), coconut, pineapple, etc.
I like them plain with sugar sprinkled on top. Drop by teaspoonful and bake at 375° until lightly brown, 7 to 9 minutes.

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, starting with liquids first.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: blueberry sour cream pie
directions: Combine sour
cream,
flour
and 3 tablespoons of brown sugar in mixing bowl.
Add
egg
and beat well.
Spoon half of this mixture into
the pie crust.
Combine blueberries and 1/2 cup of sour cream	in
a small mixing bowl, then spread evenly over sour cream
mixture.
Top
with	the remaining sour cream mixture. Bake at
for	25 minutes.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In large saucepan bring water to boil.
Add green onions, minced onion, margarine, and vinegar.
Simmer until onions and bacon are tender.
Add potatoes, Mocha Mix, and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir gently, heating through but not boiling.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses with egg, salt, pepper and parsley.
Place this mixture into uncooked jumbo shells and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread a small amount of sauce in the bottom of the pan first.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over the shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: garden fresh relish
directions: Chop all ingredients together.
Add vinegar.
Very good with meals!

title: "secret-ingredient" sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 375° for about an hour or until done. Peel and mash, adding butter and milk.
Prepare cake mix as directed, omitting oil.
Pour half of batter into mashed sweet potatoes and mix well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish (or aluminum pan will do).
Spread remainder on top of sweet potato mixture and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top looks done.
It will remind you of a favorite Thanksgiving time dessert, but I'm not telling which one!

title: vicki's chocolate mousse cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a Bundt pan.
Cool cake.
Put in freezer after cooling.
Make filling mixture.

title: porcupine hamburgers
directions: Mix together uncooked rice and ground beef.
Make into patties.
Place patties in 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Top with sauce and seasoning.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake another 10 minutes or until done to your liking.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Combine bread crumbs, milk, meat, onion, salt and pepper. Form into patties and brown.
Drain grease.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, sugar and catsup; pour over browned hamburgers.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.

title: finger paints
directions: You will also need 4 plastic cups and a medium saucepan.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir.
Allow to cool.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate bits. Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done and toothpick comes out clean.
Cut when cool.
Makes 24 bars.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients in large bowl.
Add the three cans of beans and tarragon.
Blend and chill.

title: double crust taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet until browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well.
Add taco seasoning mix and prepare according to package directions.
Set meat mixture aside.
Unroll one can of crescent rolls into two rectangles; press long sides together to make a 13 x 8-inch rectangle.
Repeat process with second can of crescent rolls; set aside.
Place rectangle of dough on an ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with 2 cups cheese. Spread ground beef mixture evenly over cheese; sprinkle with remaining 2 cups cheese.
Top with second rectangle of dough, pressing all edges to seal.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Serve with sour cream, salsa and jalapeno.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/2 of coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over top of pie.
Bake at 325° on bottom rack until pie is firm, except center.
This will finish cooking after removing from oven.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, sugar, salt and soda until light and fluffy (approximately 10 minutes).
Add flour and vinegar.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until dry.
Add sugar.
Mix evaporated milk, cornstarch, eggs and nutmeg.
Add to rice and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
