Slowly add milk.
Add lump of butter and a little vanilla. Put in casserole; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill.
If you wish to add raisins, cook on stove and drain well.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water and add other ingredients in the order given.
When mixing lemonade, follow directions on the can using amount of water called for.
For mixing orange juice only use 1 can of water.
Chill.
Add ginger ale last before serving. Serves 50.

title: rhubarb pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Mix 1/4 cup pan drippings with bread crumbs.
Save 1/2 cup.
Sprinkle the remaining crumbs into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine rhubarb, sugar, flour and cinnamon. Spoon over 1/2 the bread crumbs.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Spoon rest of rhubarb mixture over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Then sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs.

title: french toast
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Coat bread with mixture.
Cook in skillet until both sides are brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt caramels over double boiler on low heat. Add Eagle Brand milk; stir until all is smooth. Add nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on a greased flat pan. Put in freezer about 20 to 30 minutes to harden. Melt the chocolate over double boiler by directions on package. Dip in chocolate with a toothpick. Lay on wax paper to cool.

title: chicken and stuffing skillet
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add onion, bell pepper and garlic and saut until tender. Stir in flour; cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Gradually stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in pasta, chicken, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and next 8 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: hot peanut butter sauce
directions: Put cream, peanut butter and sugar on medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
This is especially good by itself or to use over cake or ice cream.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature 20 minutes.
Add garlic and cocktail sauce and mix thoroughly.
Add chopped shrimp and blend.
Chill 2-3 hours before serving.
You can also serve with cocktail sauce on top of dip, if you prefer.

title: shepherd's pie casserole
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in medium pan until done.
Brown beef or turkey in skillet with salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion salt. Drain fat from meat and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Drain green beans and place over meat.
Mash the potatoes with milk, butter and salt.
Spoon over green beans.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with gravy and biscuits.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Mix with mixer until icing will make stiff peaks (10 to 15 minutes).
Allow to cool briefly and then ice your cake!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and onions in salted water, until spinach is thawed.
Drain well.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Mix well with spinach and onions.
Bake in a greased casserole for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together until foamy.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt and sliced apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° using (9 x 13 x 2-inch) pan or two (8 x 8-inch) pans.
Remove from pans and cool.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cake and serve.

title: chicken and chickpeas
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake until chicken is coated.
Mix margarine and oil in nonstick frying pan until bubbly.
Add chicken and saute over high heat until browned on all sides.
Remove from pan and set aside. Reduce heat to medium; add green pepper and onion to pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender (1 to 2 minutes).
Add tomatoes, chickpeas and stock powder.
Stir to combine.
Return chicken to pan.
Reduce heat to low; cover pan and let simmer 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: candy balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter and sugar.
Make into small balls.
In saucepan, melt chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture; lay on wax paper or greased pan to cool.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Blend cooking oil, sugar and eggs.
Add carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 12 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting (recipe follows).

title: mashed banana and cinnamon
directions: Mash all ingredients together well.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
(It will be hot!)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter an oblong casserole dish.
Put bread in first.
Combine remaining ingredients and place in dish.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: french apple pastry(bake 30 to 35 minutes)
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Chop walnuts, add 3 Tbsp sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Unfold 1 pie crust and lightly rub with water.
Unfold 2nd pie crust and place over 1st crust forming a border.
Spread walnut mixture.
Evenly slice apples leaving the peel on.
Cut slices in half.
Arrange overlapping.
Combine cinnamon and 2 Tbsp sugar and sprinkle on apples.
Bake until crust is golden brown.
Microwave apricots preserves on high for 30 seconds of until melted.
Brush over apples and crust.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly and stir in sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan chesters
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
Place a layer in buttered or greased baking dish; add some onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Do in alternating layers until glass baking dish is filled.
Mix flour and milk together.
Pour over top of potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Check with a fork.

title: pecan catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 500 degrees.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in lukewarm water, then add yeast and dissolve.
Stir in egg; add shortening and mix in flour (the first 5 cups flour can be stirred in; the last portion will have to be kneaded).
Grease a large bowl and put dough in to rise.
If put in refrigerator, you should grease top and put foil and a damp cloth on top.
Allow 2 hours to rise, then make into desired shapes.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Prepare bacon, drain and crumble.
In large pot combine potato patties, water and bouillon.
Cover and place over medium-low heat until patties are thawed and crumbled.
Add bacon and other ingredients in order listed.
Stir until well blended, cover and cook 25 minutes, do not allow to boil.
Makes 14 servings.

title: ghoul-ade(black punch)
directions: Dissolve both envelopes of soft drink mix and 2 cups sugar in 3 quarts ice water in a nonmetal pitcher.
Add chilled ginger ale. Serve immediately.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: savory cabbage casserole
directions: Combine first 5 items.
In a large saucepan, bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Place half of rice in a greased 2-quart casserole, top with half of cabbage mixture.
Repeat layers.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beefy rice dinner
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions. In a large skillet, cook beef, celery and green pepper until meat is done. Drain. Add rice, salt and pepper. Transfer to a greased 2-quart dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: brown rice with meat loaf(baked at the same time)
directions: Prepare meat loaf as you normally would.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Brown rice and onion in margarine for a few minutes. Pour into casserole containing uncooked meat loaf.
Add soup and salt.
Stir in almonds.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: glazed brisket
directions: Place meat, seasoned with salt and pepper, onion and water in Dutch oven.
Cook until tender, about 2 1/2 hours.
Place in roasting pan and secure pineapple to top of meat with toothpicks. Boil honey, juice, sugar and water.
Pour over meat.
Roast at 425° for 35 minutes, basting every 10 minutes.
Add more water if pan gets dry.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white almond bark
directions: Line an 8x8 in. baking pan with foil. Microwave baking bars and vegetable shortening in medium, microwave-safe bowl on Medium-High (70 %) power for 1 minute, stir. Microwave an additional 10 to 20 seconds, stirring until smooth. Stir in almonds. Pour into prepared pan. Refrigerate until firm. Place morsels in a heavy-duty plastic bag. Microwave on High (100%) power for 30 sec; knead until smooth. Microwave an additional 10 to 20 seconds, kneading until smooth. Cut tiny corner from bag; drizzle over candy. Refrigerate until set. Remove foil; break into bite-size pieces.

title: rock candy
directions: Mix in large saucepan; stir until all sugar is dissolved, then cook to 310°.
Take off heat; add flavoring and food coloring. Pour onto powdered sugar covered cookie sheet.
Use your choice of flavoring.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots and onion together.
Cover with lemon and orange. Add oil and salt and pepper.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat eggs with a whisk, add flour and mix thoroughly.
Add milk, sugar and melted butter and mix good.
Pour into pie plate that has been greased with butter.
Add a generous sprinkling of nutmeg on top.
Bake in 350° oven until custard becomes firm and golden.

title: fried doughnuts - glazed
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Place rolls on foil.
With finger, push hole through center of each.
Drop biscuits into hot oil.
When one side is brown, flip and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix sugar and milk to make glaze.
Coat warm doughnuts with glaze.
Make about 3 to 4 per person.
Doughnuts may be coated in paper sack with powdered sugar or with sugar and cinnamon.
Put in bag and shake to coat.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in greased casserole.
Top with chicken. Combine undiluted soup, mayonnaise, milk, cheese and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through.

title: kerri's hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients. Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or shallow ovenproof dish. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, and baking soda with a wooden spoon.
Add eggs and pineapple. Mix well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: Mix well all ingredients and put in jar and chill.
Shake well before using.

title: easy chicken paprika
directions: Blend together first 4 ingredients; spread on chicken. Arrange chicken, not touching, in 1 layer in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 12x8 inch greased casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: texas style baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a baking dish.
Place bacon strips on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frank's veggies
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Drain canned veggies and combine all veggies with liquid. Place in fridge and serve cold.

title: strawberry delight cake
directions: Prepare cake as directions indicate on box; allow to cool. Mix berries with sugar.
Prepare pudding as indicated on box. After cake has cooled, leave in pan and punch holes with a fork all over the cake.
Pour strawberries over cake, followed by vanilla pudding.
Top the cake with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Sift half the flour, salt and baking powder; add to milk and egg mixture.
Beat batter smooth, add as much flour as needed.
Batter should be thin enough to run through a funnel.
Pour batter into deep, hot fat 375°.
Spirals and shapes can be made by criss-crossing and controlling the funnel spout with finger.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mom mom's jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 13 baking pan. Let cool completely.
Poke holes throughout cake with fork.
Mix Jell-O with 3/4 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold.
Pour into holes in cake.
Mix Dream Whip with pudding according to directions. Spread over cake.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add scalded milk (scald means to heat milk just to the boiling point, but do not allow to boil).
The pan used for scalding is easier to clean if rinsed out with hot water before adding milk.
Blend milk into egg mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until slightly shaky.
Cool.

title: beef and noodles supreme
directions: Slice beef into thin strips.
Melt the margarine, brown the beef strips.
Saute mushrooms in wine, water and bouillon for 3 minutes.
Stir flour, sugar, salt and pepper into yogurt.
Add all ingredients together.
Cook the noodles.
Serve immediately over noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, melted oleo and 3 teaspoons sugar and press into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and Cool Whip.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve over favorite salad.

title: "rolaten" (meat rolls)
directions: On each piece of meat, place a slice of onion, bacon and pickle.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Roll up and secure with metal skewers or toothpicks.
Melt 2 tablespoons shortening in Dutch oven.
Brown meat rolls.
Add water to cover and 3 bouillon cubes.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender.
Take out meat rolls. Put in 1 tablespoon Gravy Master.
Bring to a boil.
In a cup, mix up 3 tablespoons cornstarch and add enough water to form paste. Add to gravy.
Boil until thick.
Return meat rolls to gravy. Serve with noodles and vegetables.
Serves 6.

title: aunt nellie's bread pudding
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add milk and all other ingredients.
Bake in water at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: temptation cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients (flour, baking soda and salt).
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; blend well.
Make walnut size balls and press down flat in mini muffin pan.
Remove from oven and immediately press 1 peanut butter cup into each hot cookie.
The cookie should come up and surround the peanut butter cup.
Cool slightly in pan before trying to lift them out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: coconut oatmeal dreams
directions: Add everything in order.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all this well and set oven at 300° for about 2 hours. Bake in angel food cake pan (10-inch pan).
May take less time to cook due to oven.

title: betty's corn flake candy
directions: Cook sugar and syrup but do not boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes in cake with toothpick.

title: southern peach cobbler
directions: Mix together and drop on peaches.
Don't try to spread as dough!
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until dough is lightly browned. Serve warm or cold with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and soda. Add milk and eggs, beating well after each addition. Pour in rest of ingredients and bake in a 7 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain grease.
Add flour 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring well after each addition. Mix remaining ingredients and simmer in a heavy pot.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Run cranberries through food grinder or chop coarsely.
Place in bowl and sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Drain cranberries well.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mash crackers up and add sugar and butter. Mix together. Put into a 13 x 9 baking dish. Mix pudding and ice cream together with mixer and pour over cracker crust and top with Cool Whip. Freeze until you serve. Set out about 15 minutes before you serve.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Sprinkle graham crumbs on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over graham crumbs.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs.
Layer rest of ingredients.
Press gently.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually.
Add one egg and beat. Add other egg and beat.
Mix soda and milk.
Add flour, alternating with milk mixture.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla. Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked smoked picnic ham
directions: With meat saw, remove hock, then skin ham.
Boil in stockpot covered with water about 20 minutes.
Remove from water and place in baking pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: tasty potato dish
directions: Mix the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: trine's cheese log
directions: Grind all together.
Mix well.
Mold into rolls using wax paper.
Roll in chili powder.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.

title: honey mustard chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and onion in a mixing bowl.
In another small bowl combine mayo, mustard and seasonings.
Add to chicken and toss lightly.
Wonderful on croissants!

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Dice bacon and onion and cook together until done.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 3-quart casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Mix sugar, sour cream, margarine and eggs in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 1 minute.
Beat in bananas and vanilla on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in nuts.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.

title: jamaican ackara
directions: Soak the peas in lots of cold water overnight.
When you are ready to make the ackara, rub the skin off the peas and grind in a blender.
Add some hot pepper, as much as you like.
Add salt to taste.
Beat the mixture until very light.
Pour in a little water if necessary. Heat the oil and drop spoonfuls of the mixture. They will be done when golden in color.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven. Combine 3/4 c sugar, flour, 1/4 c cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add milk, butter and vanilla; mix well. Pour into a 9 in. sq. pan. Combine remaining sugar, remaining cocoa, and brown sugar. Sprinkle over batter. Carefully pour hot water over top of sugar mixture. Do Not Stir!! Bake 35-40 min.; till almost set. Remove from oven and let set for 15 min. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream. This recipe can be doubled. 6-8 servings.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, salt, pepper and oregano; then tomato sauce.
Pour in baking dish.
Layer cheese slices on top. Put biscuits on top of this.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: hot enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Mix enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and water.
Mix flour and oil together; make paste.
Mix with sauce.
Bring to a boil, then simmer.

title: creamy jello salad
directions: Boil jello and pineapple until jello dissolves.
Cool completely.
Mix in buttermilk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Garnish with fresh strawberries or maraschino cherries.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute peppers in three tablespoons of butter. Melt remaining butter in saucepan; blend in flour. Stir in milk gradually; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in remaining ingredients; heat through. Serve on toast. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine soup and broth in saucepan; bring to a boil. Boil chicken until tender. Place chicken in casserole dish, then pour broth mixture on top. Combine flour, salt, pepper, margarine and buttermilk; mix until smooth. Spoon batter over chicken and broth. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until top is slightly brown.

title: wedgie salad
directions: Combine the Blue cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire, hot sauce, salt and black pepper in a medium-size mixing bowl.
Using the back of a fork, mash the mixture together to form a thick paste.
Drizzle in the olive oil, stirring continuously with the fork until the mixture is creamy.
Add the buttermilk and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Note:
I prefer chunk bacon, cut into 1-inch cubes.

title: p.t.a.  punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill or freeze.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in the butter, add the rest of the ingredients except cheese and mix.
Place in casserole and top with grated cheese.
Cook in oven until bubbly.

title: herb roasted chicken in a bag
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in a 10 x 16-inch oven cooking bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Scatter onions and celery in bottom of bag.
Season chicken cavity with salt and pepper.
Place in bag on top of vegetables.
Combine butter, thyme, rosemary and sage in a small bowl.
Brush chicken with herbed butter.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix juice, sugar and Sprite together.
Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour juice mixture over the sherbet.
Stir gently and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line
muffin cups with paper cups. In a large	bowl, combine rolled oats and orange juice; stir well. Add
flour,
sugar,
baking
powder,
salt, baking soda, oil and egg; mix well.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups,
filling
2/3 full.
Blend 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and
sprinkle
over
batter.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes until golden brown.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Blend in oil with fork.
Add milk. Mix.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer: Mix flour, nuts and butter; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool thoroughly.

title: peppermints
directions: Boil sugar and water to soft ball stage when dropped in cold water.
Have butter and marshmallow ready and pour hot mixture over this and stir.
Add oil of peppermint and food coloring to suit taste.
Beat until quite thick, then drop on waxed paper. Makes about 50 mints.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a buttered shallow baking dish, place berries. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup sugar. In the bowl of food processor, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add butter and pulse to create a lumpy mixture. Add cream and pulse until dough forms. Dough will be soft. Spoon dough over berries. Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Drizzle over mounds of dough. Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup sugar. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until dough is lightly browned. Serve with whipped sweetened cream.

title: cocoa-cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cola and marshmallows in large bowl.
Blend at low speed of mixer.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Add cola and blend.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Sprinkle tomato slices with salt, pepper and brown sugar. Roll in cornmeal.
Fry in hot bacon drippings until golden brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli with salt and boiling water 10 to 12 minutes or 5 minutes in microwave.
Crush when cooked (2 1/2 cups).
Heat butter; cook onion and blend in flour and milk.
Stir until sauce boils and thickens.
Add bouillon, cheese and broccoli.
Reheat to boiling.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add other ingredients and simmer slowly for a long time, until well done.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: myrtle's turtles
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, melted butter and chopped nuts.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar, salt and shortening in milk.
Add eggs. Dissolve yeast in water and blend everything in flour until dough is stiff.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and cut and work until flat.
Drop into oiled pan in small rolls or cook in loaf pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: smoked salmon salad
directions: To make the vinaigrette, mix the shallot, lemon juice, vinegar, salt and pepper together.
Add the oil in a steady stream, stirring constantly with a whisk.

title: carolyn's mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken until meat falls off bone.
Crush Doritos chips and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Cut up chicken and put on top of chips.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel.
Heat until warm.
Pour over chicken.
Place cheese slices over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pansit
directions: Saute the garlic till brown.
Add
the onion, then the meat mixed with the shrimp, then all the vegetables, and
the soy sauce.
Mix until cooked, set aside.

Boil the noodles with the chicken broth and drop a little of the olive oil, a dust of garlic powder, dust of white pepper, and mix until the noodles absorb the broth, then mix the vegetables to the noodles.
Serve hot.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, milk, onion, pepper and salt together.
Make into balls and brown in 3 tablespoons of shortening and drain.
Bring catsup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, sugar and water to a boil.
Drop meat balls in and let simmer for a little while.
Put into chafing dish and keep warm.

title: oreo cookie supreme
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush 25 cookies.
Spread over butter.
Mix 2 cups Cool Whip, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over cookies.
Mix chocolate and vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread rest of Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Crush last 3 cookies and spread on top.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Dissolve baking soda and buttermilk together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add with milk.
Add preserves and nuts.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: west indies salad
directions: Mix crabmeat and onion and squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon over it. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix oil and vinegar (5 parts oil to 1 part vinegar) and stir in.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: dirt pudding
directions: You will also need 1 big clean flowerpot and 1 beautiful flower, real or fake.

title: no bake lo-fat cheesecake
directions: Cream Neufchatel cheese until smooth using a blender or fork. Add instant vanilla pudding mix and milk.
Blend to a smooth consistency.
Add flavor and juice (if desired).
Stir well.
Pour into crusts and add toppings before serving.
Cherry pie filling is good topping.
May chill or serve instantly.

title: fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Mix milk, sugar and butter in pot. Cook on high stirring frequently until it comes to a boil. Reduce heat to medium cooking for 5 minutes stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into buttered pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together using mixer for about 2 minutes. Pour into pie crust and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°. Immediately sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: a-z quick bread
directions: *Grated apples, applesauce, chopped apricots, mashed bananas, shredded carrots, cherries, dates, eggplant, figs, grapes, peaches, pears, pineapple, pumpkin, raisins, raspberries, strawberries (sliced fresh or drained), frozen yogurt, zucchini, whatever!

title: pressure cooker vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery in a pressure cooker in canola oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes with pressure cooker top rocking.
After pressure diminishes and pot can be opened, serve with any good bread.

title: monterrey bake
directions: Brown Meat with Garlic and Onion Powder.
Add other ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole.
Top with Corn Chips (or Chinese Noodles).
Bake at 375 for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: zucchini saute low-fat
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bouillon dissolved in 1/2 cup of water. Add squash and seasoning; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until squash is tender, about 15 minutes. Add corn and cook another 5 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick butter. Cream the sugar and 1 stick butter. Mix all ingredients together, then eggs, one at a time. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: mac's steak marinade(makes enough for 2 pounds of steak)
directions: *Other brands may be substituted; ingredients should include salt, pepper, garlic, celery seed, basil and marjoram.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix well and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak and slice into bite-sized pieces. Brown steak in oil in wok or skillet.
Add water, onion, garlic and ginger and cook, covered, 15 minutes.
Add peppers and cook 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce.
Add to wok and cook until clear and thick.
(Peppers should be tender-crisp.) Add tomatoes to wok; heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Delicious with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: date log
directions: In saucepan, place margarine, dates, sugar, egg and vanilla. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add cereal and pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 logs and roll in coconut.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
To serve, cut in thin slices.

title: georgia powell's chewy squares
directions: Mix and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: macaroni cheddar salad
directions: Combine the macaroni, onion, pimento, green pepper and celery; let stand in the French dressing for an hour or more.
Add the mayonnaise and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper; toss.
Serve in a salad bowl lined with crisp lettuce.

title: brownies
directions: Cream
margarine.
Add	beaten eggs and vanilla flavoring. Combine
sugar,
flour
and
cocoa.
Mix all ingredients together and
add pecans or coconut if desired.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes.
I usually double this recipe.

title: firefighter's favorite
directions: Juice left in crock-pot is served as gravy.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together and place in baking dish (greased).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion and beef.
Add salt and pepper; drain fat.
Add beans, Tabasco, catsup and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can be made a day ahead of time and baked later.

title: flan
directions: Brown (caramelize) sugar in the Pyrex dish you will be using for your baking.
This can be done on top of the stove.

title: chicken rice dish
directions: Cut up chicken; salt, pepper and flour it.
Melt oleo in heavy skillet.
Place chicken in melted butter; cook at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and add uncooked rice, sliced onions, green pepper and tomatoes; salt and pepper.
Pour broth over this and return to oven for 40 minutes.
Cover with lid.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Add onion to first 4 ingredients.
Blend all ingredients with oil and vinegar.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion and seasonings.
Place 1/3 cup meat mixture in each cabbage leaf.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place cabbage rolls in skillet; pour Hunt's tomatoes over top.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove rolls to platter.
Stir sour cream and flour into liquid in pan.
Heat through.
Serve sauce over cabbage rolls.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pesto dippers
directions: Bake muffin halves in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until crisp and golden brown at eggs.
Rub with cut side of garlic.
Combine pesto and cheese, spread on muffins.
Quarter. Serve as dippers.

title: miracle whip carrot cake
directions: Combine salad dressing, eggs and vanilla. Combine all dry ingredients then add to salad dressing mixture. Mix well.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar until blended well.
Stir in, not using mixer, the rest of the ingredients.
Fold in well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and use wax paper on bottom of pan.
Flour sides of pan.
Pour cake into pan, then sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over unbaked cake.

title: baked sauerkraut
directions: Dice and fry bacon until crisp.
Add grated onion and cook until lightly browned.
Add sauerkraut that has been rinsed and well drained.
Place in casserole.
Pour tomato juice over top. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven about 30 minutes.
Yields 5 cups.

title: best of both worlds chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in a pan at medium high.
Add the sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and let it boil for 3 minutes.
Take pan off the burner.
Add peanut butter; stir in.
Then add the oatmeal.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put into a large bowl and toss together.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Put cabbage, carrots and onions in small bowl.
Cover with sugar.
Do not stir.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Do not stir.
Cover, chill for 4 hours before serving.
Will keep for 1 month in refrigerator and will be just as crispy.

title: spicy hot wings
directions: Heat large frying skillet and grease until hot.
Mix Tabasco and pepper sauce together; let set for 5 minutes.
Take wings out; flour them lightly or as desired.
Fry until golden brown.

title: whole wheat banana-nut bread
directions: Combine flour,
salt
and soda;
set aside.
In a large bowl, cream
margarine and sugar together; add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Stir
in flour mixture, bananas and pecans until thoroughly
combined.
Pour
into
a
well-greased
and floured 8 1/2
x
4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool
in
pan
for
5 minutes, then turn out on a wire rack to cool completely.

title: apricot rice
directions: Cover raisins and apricots in water and soak 30 minutes while cooking rice.
Blend all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole.
Cook 30 minutes or until firm in 350° oven.
Makes 6 vegetarian main course meals or 10 individual servings.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop into lightly greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 24 miniature muffins.
Perfect for brunch or luncheon.

title: quick and easy salmon croquettes
directions: Remove skin from salmon.
Add well beaten egg and black pepper.
Use fork and beat up salmon; mix well.
Mixture will be juicy.
Dip by tablespoon into cracker crumbs.
Cover well and fry in small amount of canola oil until brown.
Yield:
5 or 6 medium croquettes.

title: jalapenos encuridos(pickled jalapenos)
directions: Wash jalapeno peppers.
Pack tightly in jar.
For every cup of vinegar, use 1/4 cup water, 1/4 cup olive oil, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pickling spices.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Pour over peppers, so that they are well covered.
Seal jars.
Process pint jars 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: blue cheese chutney spread
directions: Beat all ingredients except chutney and crackers in medium bowl until creamy.
Stir in chutney.
Pack into 2-cup crock or non-metal container; cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours, no longer than 2 weeks.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.
Garnish with chutney, if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: "out of this world" fruit salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Chill overnight.
Add Cool Whip before serving.
(Betcha can't eat just one bowl!)

title: cracker candy
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil; cover with a layer of soda crackers.
Combine the margarine and sugar; boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over layer of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and put back in oven until they are melted.
Remove from oven and spread the melted chocolate all over the crackers.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. In another bowl mix pudding with milk.
Combine pudding mixture and
cream
cheese mixture.
Layer with crumbled Oreo cookies
in large
clay
or
plastic
flower pot, ending with cookies, so
it has the appearance of dirt in a pot.
Stick a fresh
or artificial
flower in the center.
Refrigerate.
If using a fresh flower, wrap end in foil.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Alternately add flour and milk to the creamed mixture. Beat just until blended.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Prepare Caramel topping and pour over cake.
Cool in the pan.

title: rhubarb jello jam
directions: Cut up rhubarb and cook with 3/4 cup of water and sugar until rhubarb is tender.
Add jello and stir well.
Pour mixture into clean, hot jars.
Mixture will be runny at first, but will set in the refrigerator.
Keep refrigerated.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, salt, corn syrup, water, vinegar and butter. Cook to hard ball stage (250°).
Pour hot syrup slowly over popcorn and mix carefully to coat each kernel.
Shape mixture into balls.
You can add walnuts, gumdrops, marshmallows or semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Greasing fingers makes handling easier.
Makes 15 to 20 balls.

title: chocolate christmas cookies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add to oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough overnight. May be left in refrigerator longer. Drop by small spoon into 10x sugar, making small balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Will bake with cracks in top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix carrots, sugar, flour, cinnamon, soda and Wesson oil. Beat in eggs.
Bake at 350 degrees 45 minutes.
Makes 2 - 8-inch layers.

title: green chiles and rice frittata
directions: In small skillet over medium heat cook onions in butter until tender but not brown.
Combine rice, cheese, chiles and tomato in large bowl.
Add cooked onions.

title: chocolate caramel bars (turtles)
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining evaporated milk (1/4 cup), dry cake mix and margarine.
Mix well.
Divide dough in half.
Press 1/2 into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan (or 3-quart dish).
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle chocolate chips and 1/2 of the chopped nuts over crust. Drizzle with caramel mixture.

title: cherry peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine cherry and peach fillings in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl. Separate each biscuit into two sections.
Dip each in margarine and then in sugar and cinnamon.
Arrange on top of filling.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Bake time is 20 minutes.

title: memories of grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda, cocoa and sugar.
Add oil, hot coffee and milk and mix and add eggs and vanilla.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans.
(You can also make muffins.)
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cake in pans for 15 minutes and then complete cooling on wire rack.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in bottom of pan. Top with pecans and then place butter on top to melt. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1/2 batter in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of topping over batter.
Add remaining batter and finish with topping.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: almond green beans
directions: Place all ingredients ina 1-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 350° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Note:
A couple of small onions also may be added.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chocolate ingredients.
Spray bundt pan with PAM, pour in cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan (10 minutes).
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: tana's percolator punch
directions: Pour juices and water into bowl of electric percolator.
Add lemon juice only if a more tart punch is desired.
Put sugar, tea and cinnamon sticks into basket.
Insert pumps and basket into percolator, cover and perk.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: marinated crab claws
directions: Place crab claws in 2-quart casserole dish. In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except ice, and stir well. Pour mixture over crab claws. Pour ice cubes over top; cover and refrigerate. Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: cool and creamy fruit salad
directions: Fresh fruit is best.
Combine cream cheese, juice and rind, mixing until well blended.
Beat whipping cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Layer fruit in glass bowl.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over fruit.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Add corned beef, broken up.
Mix soup and milk together and add onion and cheese, cut into small chunks.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and sift together into a large mixing bowl.
Add raisins and walnuts to the sifted dry ingredients.
Combine beaten egg, vanilla and melted shortening and add to the flour mixture.
Dissolve soda in the undrained crushed pineapple.
Add to the flour mixture and stir just until blended.
Pour the batter into greased 9 x 4 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour or until done.
Cool bread on wire rack.
Cut bread in slices and serve spread with butter or cream cheese.
Recipe makes one loaf nut bread.

title: shrimp dip #1
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix soup with cream cheese.
Add lemon juice.
Mix until lumps are out.
Do not overmix.
Drain shrimp and pat dry.
Add to mixture.
Chill.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal, coconut and cocoa in a large bowl.
In a large saucepan combine sugar, butter, milk and salt.
Let come to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: mix for pecan or french lemon pie(makes 2 pecan or 2 french lemon pies)
directions: Use the same recipe for either pie.
For Pecan Pie, mix first 5 ingredients together with vanilla.
Pour filling into two unbaked pie crusts and sprinkle top of pies with chopped pecans. For French Lemon Pie, omit vanilla and pecans and add juice and finely ground rind of 4 lemons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Filling will be slightly soft in center.)

title: epps' vacation quiche
directions: Layer all the ingredients in the pie shell.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or more.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Make cake by the box directions.
Let cool completely.
Poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Mix pineapple and milk.
Spread over cake, then top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican rice
directions: Wash and dry rice between towels.
Heat shortening in heavy skillet over medium heat (325° to 350°) on controlled burner.
Add onion.
Cook, stirring frequently, until rice is browned and onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce to low heat (175° to 200°).
Cook for 30 minutes. Makes about 6 servings.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: In dish, add rice, sausage, soups and mushrooms.
Stir.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil.
Stir and bake 15 minutes, uncovered, when baking for 15 minutes.

title: basic pie crust
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in food processor, fitted with metal blade.
Cut both types of fat into 1/2-inch pieces and drop into processor.
Process for about 3 seconds, until flour and fat are barely combined.
Remove the ice cubes and pour ice water into processor.
Process again for 2 or 3 seconds, just until dough forms cohesive mass.
If dough doesn't hold together, add a few more drops of very cold water and process briefly.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Cut chicken to bite size and add almonds.
Place in buttered casserole in layers.
Mix soup, milk, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder and pour over chicken and broccoli. Brown bread crumbs. Combine with grated cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and peanut butter. Beat in the sugars.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Arrange by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Press flat with a floured spoon or mark with a floured fork.
Bake until firm (about 10 minutes). Makes 60.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cut squash and onion and cook until tender in a small amount of water. Break up lightly. Add milk, egg, butter, cheese, salt and sugar. Mix. Pour in greased baking dish and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bananas; mix well.
Slice and mix in bananas when ready to serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine milk, egg substitute, margarine, corn, cheese, chiles, onion and red pepper.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 16 servings.

title: jello ice cream
directions: Chill evaporated milk thoroughly.
Mix jello with boiling water. Add cold water and sugar. Dissolve well.

Using a blender, whip the evaporated milk until frothy. Pour into ice cream freezer along with crushed berries, salt and enough milk to fill freezer. Chill about 1 hour and freeze according to freezer directions.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar; add oil, water and pumpkin.
Add baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, ginger and flour until mixed well.
Add nuts and pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough.
Otherwise, just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a microwave-safe dish or pan. Sprinkle with melted butter and the herbs of your choice. Microwave on High power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes on High, until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocado with a fork.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except mayonnaise.
Spread mayonnaise over top of dip to keep it from darkening.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute in oil the onions, celery and green pepper.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and vinegar and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and peas and cook just until heated through.
Serve over rice.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cut cream cheese into Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon juice. Blend well, then add fruit cocktail and crushed peaches.
Stir in pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 pie shells and chill.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Fry potatoes in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings until done.
Beat eggs with minced garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour into skillet with potatoes, cheese and green chiles; cook until firm, stirring constantly.
Heat tortillas, one at a time, on burner until soft, about 1 second on each side.
Stack on paper towel.
Roll 2 tablespoons egg mixture in each tortilla.
May serve with salsa.

title: tamale bites(appetizer meatballs)
directions: Combine corn bread crumbs, 1/2 cup enchilada sauce and salt. Add ground beef, mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Heat tomato sauce and remaining enchilada sauce and pour over meatballs.
Serve.

title: lobster sauce(salsa di aragostina)
directions: This is another personal favorite.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, fry sausage until cooked.
Remove sausage; drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and pepper in reserved fat 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine cheese and flour.
Stir in sausage, green pepper and onion.
Spread in pie crust shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and filling is set.
Cut in wedges like pie.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs with 1 stick margarine.	Press into a 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Beat	eggs,
sticks margarine and powdered sugar for about 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over crust.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool	Whip over
pineapple.
Garnish
with nuts and cherries. Drizzle with chocolate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil over medium-high heat in large skillet.
Lightly salt and pepper pork chops and brown in oil.
Lightly grease large baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine soup and broth.
Stir to mix.
Layer potatoes and onions; lightly salt and pepper.
Add pork chops in baking pan.
Pour soup and broth over pork chops.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.

title: hot weather punch
directions: Put orange juice and lemonade concentrates into a 2 1/2 to 3-quart pitcher.
Add water, nectar and pineapple juice, stirring. Chill.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: heath pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, soda cracker crumbs and butter well.
Press in a square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and set aside.

title: refreshing punch
directions: Mix all together and add water to make 2 gallons.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: raw vegie pizza
directions: Flatten the rolls on jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together the mayonnaise, cream cheese, dill, pepper, garlic and dressing mix; spread on crust.
Garnish with finely chopped vegetables (any combination of raw vegies).
You need only a few pieces of each vegie for a nice color combo.
Chill overnight.
Serve whole on a tray, or cut into little bite size pieces.

title: grasshopper dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and liqueur.
Pour 1 cup into a bowl and chill until slightly thickened.
Pour remaining gelatin mixture in a 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm, at least 3 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: pig picklin cake
directions: Blend cake mix, mandarin oranges and juice, oil and eggs together about 2 minutes at medium speed.
Grease and lightly flour 3 (8 1/2 or 9-inch) layer pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. When cake is cool, put Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and juice and vanilla instant pudding together and blend well.
Spread between and on top of layers.
Refrigerate at least 3 days before cutting. Keep in refrigerator.
It must "pickle" for at least 3 days.

title: pronto pups(corn dogs)
directions: Mix all ingredients except wieners.
Dip wieners in mixture, making sure wiener is covered.
Fry in deep fryer at 370° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn once so they are golden brown on both sides. A wooden stick inserted in wiener makes it easier to handle.

title: hershey bar torte
directions: Mix graham
crackers, sugar and oleo.
Pat into pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: "puppy chow"(delicious people snack)
directions: Mix together oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Chex.
Stir until coated.
Put in brown paper sack with confectioners sugar.
Shake.

title: potato soup
directions: Add all together except the evaporated milk in large pot and cook until tender.
Take masher and mash the vegetables.
(You can also place in blender and puree.) Let the entire mixture cool completely.
When cold, add the evaporated milk and reheat.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add enough water to fruit liquid to make 2 cups and add to gelatin.
Let Jell-O gel slightly.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and congeal.

title: fagioli all'uccelletto
directions: Combine oil, garlic and sage in a skillet.
When the garlic is golden, remove it and add the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and cook for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring often.
Drain the beans and put them in the skillet, then let cook on medium heat for about 7 to 8 minutes.
Before serving, add freshly ground black pepper.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, on medium speed.
Mix well.
At low speed, add flour and soda.
Add sour cream and flavoring.
Mix well. Cook in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Arrange layers of cheese and bacon in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Combine eggs with remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour over cheese and bacon.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes (or until knife inserted in center comes out clean).
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: apricot crisp
directions: Cut apricot halves in half.
Combine with the 2 tablespoons of syrup and arrange in a quart casserole dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients mixing until crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with ice cream.

title: sausage, peppers and potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients in large pan; drizzle with oil.
Add water and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, mixing occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: double layered pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in a large bowl; whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip; spread on bottom of crust. Pour milk and pudding mix in bowl.
Beat with whisk until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: "little barbara cookies"
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg together.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Roll out and cut in desired shape.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Score chicken or beef.
Marinate overnight or several hours. Grill or broil meat.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes, until slightly thickened.

title: philly-cheese sandwich
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Stack beef and onion on bottom half of each bun.
Cut cheese slices in half and place 4 halves on top of each sandwich.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted.
Top each sandwich with remaining bun.
Serve with chips and pickle strips.

title: chicken and peppers
directions: In large skillet, heat olive oil.
Add chopped up chicken to heat.
Cut peppers into thin slices and add to chicken along with one tablespoon butter.
Then add vinegar, basil and oregano; let simmer 1 hour or until chicken is done.
In a large pot, boil water.
Add spaghetti.
Cook until done and drain.
Add 1 tablespoon of butter to drained spaghetti and stir.
Add the chicken and peppers and sauce from skillet.
Stir and serve.

title: nutty cream cheese spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring until blended. Chill 10 minutes. Shape into log. Lightly coat top
and sides with pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat and add gradually eggs, sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla. Add and mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Fold in zucchini, walnuts and raisins.
Bake for 55 minutes in oven at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves, 3 x 9-inches.

title: jello pie
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O for 2 minutes until dissolved. Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups. Add to Jell-O, stirring until thickened. Remove any remaining ice cubes. Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Refrigerate 10 minutes. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: crunchy choco-peanut candy
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients; cook and stir over medium heat until smooth and well blended.
Remove from heat. Stir in noodles and 1 cup nuts.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut up onion and saute in butter until tender.
Add flour and stir.
Add salt, stir in milk and cook on medium-low until thick. Add cheese.
Slice potatoes thin, place 1/2 in 8 x 11-inch dish. Add sauce, then rest of potatoes, then rest of sauce.
Bake at 350°, covered, 35 minutes and uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine
frozen
strawberries,
sugar
and beaten eggs. Cook over
low heat until well heated and beginning to bubble. Pour in package
of jello and let cool.
Whip evaporated milk and fold into
strawberry
mixture.
Pour into crusts and top with whipped cream.

title: smoked sausage dinner
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion, green pepper and sausage until onion is tender and sausage is heated through.
Drain off fat.

title: sherry's potato casserole
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.

title: veal cutlets maryland
directions: Rub cutlets with melted butter, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll cutlets in cracker crumbs; dip into beaten eggs, then back into crumbs.
Melt butter in shallow pan and cook cutlets to a golden brown on both sides.
Pour cream and milk over cutlets.
Cover pan tightly and cook in 300° oven for 1 hour. Remove meat.
Thicken sauce in pan with a few fine cracker crumbs and serve hot.

title: ho-made hoedowns
directions: Sandwich two snack crackers together with a generous amount of peanut butter.
Press together so peanut butter spreads to edge. Using tongs, dip crackers into melted coating.
Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in heavy iron skillet.
In a large bowl, mix the remaining ingredients; pour into bubbling margarine.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: abby's pottsville pickle
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, celery and red peppers.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Makes 14 pints.

title: yeast bread
directions: In large bowl put 2 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
Heat water and oil until very warm.
Don't boil your water but have it very warm.
Pour into flour mixture; mix well.
Add rest of flour; knead well.
Grease bowl and turn over to grease both sides.
Then cover and let rise to double.
Punch down; knead.
Make rolls or 2 loaves.
Put in greased pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in very deep baking dish.
Set in a 350° oven to melt.
Make a batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and milk.
When mixed, pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Empty can of peaches with juice and 1/2 cup of sugar on top of batter.
Do not stir! Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge or icing
directions: Melt butter. Add milk, vanilla and cocoa; stir. Pour in bowl with confectioners sugar. Mix 3 minutes on high speed.
Add nuts. Pour in pan and place in refrigerator for 2 hours. Cut and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute hamburger and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano and simmer 20 minutes.

While it simmers, cook the noodles in boiling salt water for 15 minutes. Butter a casserole dish and alternate layers of noodles, cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan, ending with a layer of sauce and Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and vegetable salad
directions: Add all ingredients.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: pineapple 'n guava mold
directions: In small saucepan, combine gelatin, sugar and reserved juice from pineapple.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, until gelatin and sugar are dissolved, stirring constantly.
Transfer to large bowl; stir in crushed pineapple, nectar, sour cream and salt until well combined.
Chill 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Coat an 8 cup mold or bowl with nonstick cooking spray; pour in gelatin-pineapple mixture.
Chill 8 hours or overnight until firm.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add flour.
Roll out dough and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for about 10 minutes.

title: crostini with tomato pesto
directions: Slice the baguette crosswise into 1/2 inch thick slices. Place on baking sheet.
Brush one side of each slice with olive oil and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 5 minutes.
Turn each slice over and bake for an additional 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with Tomato Pesto Spread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.

title: apple potatoes
directions: Place all the ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 35 to 40 minutes. Mash as you would for regular mashed potatoes.
Serve with roast pork or pork chops.

title: sunday chicken and dressing
directions: Saute onions in butter. Heat broth and undiluted soups. Pour over corn bread crumbs. Add onions and celery. Mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Pour half of the dressing in a greased 9 x 10-inch casserole. Add chicken and pour the other half of the dressing over chicken. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy crescent rolls
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons cheese with chicken.
Put 2 tablespoons of mixture on wide part of triangle; roll up.
Place in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining cheese, soup and milk.
Heat until blended. Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over rolls.
Cook at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Top with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, blending well.
Put into a ring mold and chill until firm.
Best overnight.
To serve, turn out on a plate and fill center with 1 jar of strawberry preserves.
Use on Ritz crackers.
Serves 40 to 50.
Keeps well for weeks.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa and oleo in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (depends on whether you like soft or chewy or done).

title: mother's apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and egg.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter bean salad
directions: Add beans to boiling water; boil for 10 minutes, then rinse immediately with cool water.
Mix beans, celery, onions and walnuts with mayonnaise.
Chop eggs and add to top of beans.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Refrigerate.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: sweet potatoes with crunchy topping
directions: Drain and mash potatoes.
Mix other ingredients and add to potatoes.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine milk, pie filling mix, pumpkin, spice and whipped topping in a deep narrow bottom bowl.
Beat at lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill until set, at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and pecans, if desired.

title: original toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in the semi-sweet morsels.
Drop by rounded measured teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: scripture cake
directions: Read Proverbs 23:1.
In order to make cake, look up scriptures and find out the ingredients.
God Bless!

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients using only 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini and sour cream
directions: Slice washed, unpeeled zucchini into thin rounds. Simmer, covered, in a small amount of water for 6 to 8 minutes, shaking the pan frequently. Drain. Combine sour cream, butter, 2 tablespoons grated cheese, salt, pepper and paprika.
Stir over low heat to melt cheese.
Remove from heat and mix in chives. Toss lightly with zucchini.

Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with crumbs (optional) and sprinkle with additional cheese. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes. Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated but increase the baking time to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
(Microwavable.)

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix together in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or longer until light brown on top. Serves 3 to 4.

title: italian dunkers
directions: Butter buns open face.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown.
Good with tomato soup.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in salted water 5 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar, pepper, celery seed, dry mustard and turmeric.
Add cucumbers to boiling mixture and boil until cucumbers change color.
Seal boiling hot. Makes 8 pints.

title: mai tais
directions: Mix together in a glass.
Add ice cubes and fruit garnish.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat sugar and pineapple to a boil.
Add jello and cool in refrigerator.
Whip cream cheese and milk.
Whip Dream Whip as directed.
Whip jello and cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Set overnight.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook until soft ball stage.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Place in a large kettle, covering with water.
Add garlic powder, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender.
Do not drain water.
In a blender, blend about 2 cups of the soup and return to the kettle (this makes the soup thicker).
Add cheese and continue to cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir in cocoa and baking soda; blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs, and remaining oil until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons fat.
Add onions and brown.
Add potatoes and about 1 1/2 cups water or enough to cover.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: france's spinach salad
directions: Mix and toss all together.
Just before serving, pour dressing over all.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into a large mixer bowl.
Beat until well mashed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart baking dish in oven.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together and pour in dish over melted butter.
On top of this, carefully place the fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes or until top is brown and crusty.

title: sweet potatoes surprise balls
directions: Boil the potatoes in salted water until fork-tender; drain well, reserving some liquid if needed.
Mash the potatoes and mix with the rest of the ingredients, using reserved liquid if potato mixture is too dry.
Using hands and a large spoon, spread potatoes around large size marshmallows. Roll in either crushed corn flakes or coconut.
Bake at 350° just until marshmallows get soft.
Serve warm.

title: ruth's crunchy double chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and salt.
Set aside. In a large mixing bowl, beat together the sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in dry ingredients, mixing until thoroughly combined. Add 2 cups of crushed corn flakes, chocolate and peanut butter morsels.
Drop by teaspoon and roll in remaining crushed corn flakes, coating completely.
Place 2-inches apart on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and blend well.
Form into small meat balls and place in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch pan. May be frozen until needed.

title: french crisps
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla and beat.
Add flour.
Mix and spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and spread on cookies as soon as removed from oven.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Cut while warm.

title: salsa steak
directions: Cook steak in skillet on low heat.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until done on one side.
When you turn steak to cook, add onion slices, green pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Boil water in heavy pot; add butter and stir until melted. Add flour and salt all at once, stirring and cooking a minute or so until mixture forms a soft ball that does not separate. Remove from heat; cool 10 minutes and add eggs one at a time, beating vigorously after each. Form 12 to 15 spoonfuls of batter into smooth capsule shapes on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in 450° oven 15 minutes, then lower to 325° and bake another 25 minutes.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Rinse fish.
Place in large casserole dish and season.
Pour lemon juice over.
Heat oil in small saucepan and stir in flour.
Add yogurt and stir until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Arrange onions over steaks.
Pour sauce over it all. Bake for 15 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Check by fork. Sprinkle over the dried parsley.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Layer corn and cracker crumbs. Mix eggs and milk. Pour over all. End with layer of crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: all-american cornbread
directions: Scald cream with butter.
Add to thoroughly mixed dry ingredients.
Mix in eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: grilled spicy chicken breast fillets
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Set aside.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place in shallow glass dish. Add lime juice mixture and stir to coat chicken pieces thoroughly.
Cover dish and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours; stir several times while marinating to keep chicken well coated.
On a preheated outdoor grill, cook chicken, turning once, 6 to 7 minutes until done.

title: della's banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix well, then add eggs and milk. Cook until starting to thicken and add vanilla. Finish cooking until real thick.
Layer bananas, wafers and pudding. Cool before serving.

title: curried dofu gravy
directions: Melt margarine and add flour, stirring until margarine melts. Add water slowly, stirring continuously.
Dice the Dofu and add with remaining ingredients.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Saute half cup of bell pepper and onions in butter or margarine.
Brown pork chops on both sides in separate frying pan. Pour consomme beef and onion soups on 2 cups rice in saucepan.
Let cook for about 30 minutes or until rice is halfway done, uncovered, in oven on 300° to 350°.
Take saucepan out of oven and spread pork chops over rice.
Cut strips of bell pepper and strips of onions on top of pork chops.
Bake in preheated oven, covered with foil, for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine
potatoes,
cup
butter, soup, onion, sour cream and
cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Stir remaining butter into cornflakes and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix the sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add the vinegar and water; stir the mixture until it is smooth.
Cook it for 5 minutes, then add the beets and let it stand for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, bring the beets to a boil and add the butter. (Omit the salt when using canned beets which have been salted.)

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Cook until thick.
Stir in peaches and pour into prebaked pie shell.
Chill and serve with Cool Whip topping.
(Add sugar to peaches if they are not sweet enough.)

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and onions; drain.
Add milk to soup and mix together.
Put potatoes in casserole dish; add soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Grate cheese or lay slices of cheese on top. Heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: patsy's coconut balls
directions: Melt in skillet margarine and sugar.
Add dates; cook and stir two minutes.
Turn heat off.
Slowly add egg, milk and salt.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla, cereal and pecans. Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat; cut up scallions finely.
Zap all ingredients in a blender.
Heat in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Serve hot on round firm crackers.

title: vicki's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding beaten eggs last.
Pour into a 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together pumpkin, sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Mix in flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
May add chocolate chips, chopped nuts or raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: easy veggie soup
directions: In a large pot, empty can of juice; match with one can water. Heat to boil while preparing veggies.
Add veggies to juice when it reaches a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, then lower heat to simmer and cook until veggies are tender.
Season with black pepper and garlic powder to taste.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; place potatoes in saucepan and cover with water.
Boil potatoes until tender; stir potatoes in pan; break up large pieces; do not let boil dry.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Simmer; add margarine.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: If you use the frozen hash brown, press between paper towels to remove moisture.
Press hash browns into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate to form a crust.
Drizzle melted butter over crust.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cookies are done when they spring back like cake.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Boil berries, oranges and lemons for 20 minutes.
Strain.
Add sugar and spices.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday ham
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 1 tablespoon of juice.
Combine sugar, mustard and juice.
Place ham in a roasting pan.
Spread the sugar mixture on top of ham.
Top with whole pineapple, with cherries in center of pineapple and bake slowly according to weight of the ham.

title: baked tuna (or salmon) croquettes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. About 30 minutes before serving, grease cookie sheet. Drain liquid from tuna into a medium bowl. Add crumbs and 1/2 cup wheat germ. Blend well. Stir in Miracle Whip, canned milk, onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper and tuna and mix well. Sprinkle wheat germ onto waxed paper. Shape tuna mixture into 8 croquettes. Roll in wheat germ. Place on cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 375°. Serve with tartar sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: santa fe chicken and dressing
directions: Combine stuffing and next five ingredients in a large bowl; toss until combined.
Add soup, corn, sour cream and cumin to stuffing mixture; stir well.
Spread in a lightly greased 2 qt. baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and chopped onion and drain fats. Add pork and beans, white lima beans, kidney beans, ketchup, brown sugar, salt, mustard and vinegar.
Mix together and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked clam dip
directions: On low heat, simmer butter, onion and garlic until soft.
Add clams, reserved juice, lemon juice, oregano, Tabasco sauce and pepper, then add bread crumbs.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and strips of Muenster cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Mix cabbage, onion and bell pepper in large bowl.
Brown ground chuck and mix with cabbage.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: southern style scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel potatoes and cut into very thin slices.
Melt together bacon drippings and margarine.
Arrange a single layer of potatoes in bottom of a greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle with some of the bacon drippings and margarine.
Sprinkle lightly with some of the flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers using remaining ingredients, except cream and milk.
Pour cream over potatoes.
Add milk, if necessary, to barely cover potatoes.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Uncover, raise oven temperature to 400° and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until browned on top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in an 8-inch round pan.
Combine oatmeal, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be microwaved 15 to 20 minutes or until apples are done.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer all ingredients (but eggs) in saucepan for 10 minutes. Put eggs in jar and cover with hot mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Standard Angel Food recipe or cake mix for Angel food works just fine.
Add a 1/2 cup of triple sifted Hershey's Cocoa Powder to an angel food cake mix.
Fold in after beating egg mixture almost to complete.
Bake according to package instructions.
