Allow to cool completely.
Carefully cut angel food cake into several layers -- frost each layer with chocolate sauce.
Dust top with cocoa after frosting and then shave curls of chocolate onto top. Chill milk chocolate bar and then use carrot peeler to shave curls off bar, arrange in random manner.
Looks great with white chocolate on dark chocolate sauce.

title: dad's orange nut bread
directions: Combine butter, orange juice, orange rind, dates, sugar, egg, and pecans.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Blend the two mixtures together and pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ore-ida potato casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream, frozen potatoes with onions and peppers and Cheddar cheese all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Crush the corn flakes and mix with melted butter.
Put on top of the potatoes.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss vegetables, bacon pieces, and pecans in bowl.
Mix dressing into salad until coated.
Let stand several hours or overnight, serve chilled.
Dressing can be made ahead.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Peel and dice squash.
Simmer in broth until tender.
Puree. Return to stove and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
Adjust seasonings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Mix pudding, cake mix, oil, sour cream and eggs together.
Put half of batter into a tube pan.
Sprinkle half of nut mixture on top.
Add the rest of the batter.
Sprinkle with the remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well and chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken smothered in mushroom sauce
directions: Flour chicken and fry in iron skillet in about 1-inch of Crisco.
Drain.
Place brown pieces in a large casserole, cover with sauce.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish except butter. Place butter slices on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sticky pecan rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine baking soda, granulated sugar, salt, yeast and 1 cup of the flour.
Place buttermilk and oil in pan over medium heat (about 120°); add to flour mixture and beat with an electric mixer on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of remaining flour and beat with a wooden spoon until smooth. Sprinkle some of the remaining 1/2 cup of flour on a board.
Turn dough out onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes, adding flour as needed.
Let dough rest on board while preparing pans.
In a small bowl, combine water, 4 tablespoons melted butter and 1/2 cup of the brown sugar. Distribute mixture equally among 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups; top mixture with chopped pecans.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place a layer of beans and onions in a casserole.
Mix soup, mushrooms and almonds.
Pour over beans and onions.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: clam marinara soup from spain
directions: In a 3 quart saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add mushrooms and green peppers. Cook until tender. Stir in wine and simmer for 1 minute. Stir in tomato soup, broth, 1/2 cup water, clams and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Simmer 15 minutes, or until clams are open; stir occasionally. Discord only unopened clams.

title: green beans far east
directions: Heat beans; add chestnuts and heat through.
Cook onions separately in butter until tender, not brown!
Add sugar, salt, vinegar, pepper and sour cream; heat through, do not boil.
Drain beans, put in bowl and top with sour cream mix.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix margarine, peanut butter and sugars, mixing well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on pan; flatten with fork or drop by teaspoon on pan and flatten just a little.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes and while still warm put chocolate Kiss on top.
Cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in thin strips.
Mince garlic and onion.
Cut flowers off broccoli and set aside.
Cut celery, carrots and broccoli stems in bite size pieces.
Heat wok to 425°, add 1 tablespoon oil and heat.
Add chicken, stir-fry at high temperature until golden brown.
Remove chicken.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until clear.
Add broccoli stems, carrots and celery; stir-fry until crunchy.
Add soy sauce and chicken stock.
Mix cornstarch and water, add to vegetables until slightly thickened.
Add broccoli flowers and chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: easy cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a hot large skillet, brown meat, stirring often. Drain off fat.
Reserve meat.
In a medium size bowl, combine spaghetti sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
In another bowl, combine eggs, cottage cheese and salt.

In a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole, spoon 1/3 of the sauce mixture. Top with half of the noodles, all of the cheese mixture, 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese slices and 1/3 of the sauce. Repeat layering using remaining noodles, ground beef and sauce.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover.
Top with remaining Mozzarella.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil in small saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Cool.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray jelly roll pan with Pam.
Melt brown sugar and butter or margarine in a pan with the cinnamon.
Let dough rise until double. Punch down and roll out on floured surface.
Pour mixture on dough, roll up and cut in 3/4 to 1-inch pieces.
Place pecan pieces on pan.
Put the cut pieces of cinnamon rolls on pecans.
Let rise. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tabboulehlebanese wheat salad
directions: Rinse bulgur well and cover with fresh cold water to soak for about 30 minutes while you chop the vegetables.
When bulgur grains are nicely plump, drain them, squeezing out as much water as you can between your hands.

title: date bars
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together the flour and baking powder.
Add salt and sugar; stir well again.
Add dates.
Mix well with fingers to separate dates.
Stir in chopped pecans and coconut.
In a small mixing bowl, beat eggs enough to blend yolks and whites.
Add to flour mixture with butter and vanilla; stir to mix thoroughly.
Turn into a greased and floured square pan (9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch).
Bake in a preheated 325° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, 45 minutes.
These are really good.

title: packed potatoes
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Do not overcook.
Drain. Brown sausage in skillet with onions and pepper.
Drain off fat. Add cheese, soup, milk and pimentos to sausage mixture.
Mix well. Add noodles.
Bake in casserole dish in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: one step lasagna
directions: In 2-quart glass casserole, cook ground meat on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and 1/2 cup water and salt.
Microwave, covered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Layer sauce, half of noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese and half the grated cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave, tightly covered, on High for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: grandma henrietta raleigh's corn pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt. Stir in eggs, then add milk and corn. Stir and add melted butter until well blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: circus wagons
directions: Take 1/2 of a graham cracker.
Cover one side with pink icing. Place animal cookie on top of icing.
Place chocolate chip or gum drop in both corners (wheels).
Take tube of icing and make strips up and down over cracker bars.
Your circus wagon is finished! Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of pan; dilute soup with water.
Pour over rice.
Dip chicken in melted butter and lay on top of rice and soup.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Blend all with electric beater.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with Munchos or Bugles, or anything that you would use for a regular dip.
May be frozen.

title: celery seed slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine cabbage, carrot and green pepper.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, celery and bacon bits; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Makes approximately 12 to 16 servings.

title: spiced chicken legs (or wings)
directions: Place chicken in one layer in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until browned, about 1 hour.
Turn occasionally.
Drain off fat.
With slotted spoon, transfer wings to warm Garlic Sauce.
Mix well.
Serve with hot red peppers.

title: barbara's banana cake
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, banana, eggs, vanilla and milk. Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to banana mixture. Add nuts and/or chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.
Frost with White Creamy Icing.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice in 2 cups water.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Combine all ingredients and put in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine on low speed for 30 seconds to soften.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Put dry ingredients into beaten mixture.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Roll in the 2 tablespoons sugar and place on an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes before removing from pan.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and brown rice until golden brown.
Add can of tomato sauce, onion, chicken bouillon and 2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add more water, if needed.

title: easy tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in skillet; drain.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread out evenly to cover the bottom of the pan. Spread 6 corn tortillas on top of meat.
Spread beans on top of tortillas.
Sprinkle chopped onion over the beans.
Sprinkle a layer of cheese over onion.
Put 6 more corn tortillas on top of cheese.
Spread soup over the tortillas as if icing a cake.
Slice tomatoes and layer on top of soup.
Sprinkle more cheese on top of tomato layer.
Cover with foil.
Cook for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove foil and cook another 10 minutes to crispen the cheese.

title: potato-carrot casserole
directions: In a greased casserole, combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, sugar, salt and pepper. Drizzle butter over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until carrots are tender.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup, green pepper, pimiento and macaroni to ground beef.
Place 1/2 of mixture in greased 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Top with rest of macaroni mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: scottsbluff eggs
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; beat until well mixed. Pour into baking dish.
If desired, prepare 2 batches for brunch for 16.
(Can be made ahead.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.)

title: chocolate caramel pecan squares
directions: Melt evaporated milk and caramels (use double boiler or microwave).
Mix remaining ingredients (mixer may be used).
Put half of cake mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Add caramel mixture and 6 ounces chocolate chips. Crumble rest of cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Melt butter in hot pan; add onion and green pepper.
Stir until just cooked al dente.
Stir in curry powder.
Add shrimp; cook 2 minutes.
Turn shrimp; cook 2 more minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Serve over rice.
Great for drop in company! Recipe can be prepared in under 10 minutes if you use Minute rice.

title: baked red snapper parmesan
directions: Season the fillets with salt and pepper and place in a well-buttered baking dish.
Cover and place in a preheated 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine the onion, sour cream, Parmesan cheese and mustard.
Spread this sauce over the fish and place under a hot broiler until nicely browned.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grind corn and pour on 2 cups hot milk. Let stand 1 hour. Add eggs, cup milk, butter, sugar and salt to taste. Put in buttered baking dish. Put dish in pan of hot water. Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: hot spicy lemonade punch
directions: In slow cooking pot combine cranberry juice, sugar, lemonade concentrate, water and honey.
Tie cloves and cinnamon in small cheesecloth square.
Add spice bag and lemon slices to juices. Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove spice bag.
Keep hot in slow cooking pot.
Makes 9 to 10 cups.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut zucchini lengthwise.
Scoop out to 1/4-inch.
Chop pulp.
Brown hamburger.
Drain fat.
Stir in pulp, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup sauce and egg; mix well.
Place shells in shallow dish.
Spoon meat mixture into shells.
Pour sauce over and around zucchini. Cover and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: linguine with sweet pepper sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet and add the peppers, onions, garlic, shallots and basil or oregano.
Cook on medium-low until vegetables are soft, approximately 20 minutes.
Stir in honey and vinegar.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy 1 1/2 quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 4 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add 1/2 jar marshmallow and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chips.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Cool and cut.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with Season All.
Melt butter and brown meat. Pour in beef broth.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Stir together and pour over meat.
Cook until sauce starts to thicken (approximately 1 to 2 minutes).
Add tomatoes.
Do not cook any longer!
Pour over rice.

title: euricka's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually; continue beating.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine sour cream and soda; set aside.
Combine flour and nutmeg.
Slowly add dry ingredients to butter mixture. Add sour cream mixture and vanilla; mix well.
Chill dough 1 hour. Roll dough, about 1/3 at a time, to desired thickness, about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost and decorate as desired.
Makes 16 dozen.

title: mona's jelly roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form. Fold yolks into whites.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; fold into egg mixture.
Spread batter evenly in greased and lightly floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch sheet pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately loosen sides and turn out on towel sprinkled with sifted confectioners sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll cake and towel together; cool on rack.
Unroll; spread with favorite filling.
Roll up.
Makes ten one-inch slices.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound 8 chicken breasts very thin.
Place teaspoon butter in center of each.
Combine chives, salt and pepper on each breast and overlap sides so butter is enclosed (the flesh will adhere).
Beat egg whites and milk together.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and then egg white mixture, then bread crumbs, coating well. Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Deep fry in hot corn oil until well browned 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Serve hot.

title: saucy carrots
directions: Drain carrots.
Put other ingredients in small pan in order listed.
Heat, stirring constantly, until blended.
Add carrots to sauce and heat slowly until ready to serve.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat 1 minute longer.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Then spread on a tortilla only a couple of spoonfuls of the mixture. Roll like a jelly roll. Cut about 1-inch thick.

title: red or green christmas pickles
directions: Mix together and pour over cucumbers and let set overnight. Next morning boil cucumbers in mixture for 40 minutes.
Divide and add green food coloring to half and red food coloring to other half.
Pour into jars and seal.
Very pretty and good too.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cut loaf of bread lengthwise; butter lightly.
Mix all ingredients well; spread mixture on bread.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and oregano.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add Italian spices and garlic, if you wish.

title: onion-cheese supper bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Lightly coat a 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan with the cooking spray and set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding, then add remaining ingredients. Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large pot melt the margarine with the seasoned salt and flour until bubbly.
Slowly add the milk and stir until smooth and thick.
Add the clams with liquid.
Add grated carrots, drained and diced potatoes and onion.
Add parsley and seasonings.
Add sour cream and stir hard.
Simmer 1 hour.
Can be frozen.
Can add milk if too thick.

title: deluxe ginger cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Add sugar and shortening.
Combine vinegar, buttermilk and molasses. Stir in flour mixture.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add pure vanilla and pure lemon; mix well.
Put into deep pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable batter
directions: Mix flour and beer.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 hours.
(Beer breaks down the gluten in flour for a light, delicate batter.)
Dip vegetables in batter and fry or deep fry (375°).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and mayo.
Layer in serving dish (such as glass pie pan).
Spread cocktail sauce over.
Add cheese, shrimp, tomatoes and onions.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: california potatoes
directions: Mix and break potatoes into a large bowl and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Reserve broth.
Cook rice as directed on package, using broth of chicken instead of water.
Saute onion, pimento and water chestnuts in butter for a few minutes.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes in a large covered casserole.
Freezes well.
Serves 12.

title: money saver homemade biscuit mix
directions: Mix flour and shortening on low speed of electric mixer until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Store in a covered container at room temperature.

title: bloomin onion
directions: Peel outer skin of onion, but leave root intact.
Remove onion from hot water and immerse in ice water.
Put flour into paper bag (may also use cajun seasoning).
Heat oil to 375-380°. If oil isn't hot enough, it will be greasy.
Serve with sauce.

title: chicken for two
directions: Cook chicken in pan until done.
Dice chicken breasts and add potatoes, carrots, cream of mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: bananas in palm beach
directions: Preheat oven
to
In medium skillet melt butter. Add bananas
and
saute until tender.
Wrap each in a slice of Muenster cheese and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon
sugar and bake in oven until cheese is slightly melted,
about 6 minutes.
Garnish with strawberries and serve immediately.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix altogether in the order given.
Put in muffin tins with liners.
Bake at 325° in convection oven about 25 minutes.
Yield: 168 muffins.

title: homemade pancake syrup
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar on very low fire; heat, stirring until sugar is all melted.
Add water and remaining cup of sugar.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add a little maple flavoring.

title: apple crisp
directions: Simply wrap pie dough around the pared apple or peach and sprinkle sugar to taste on top, plus cinnamon and nutmeg and several swirls of Karo syrup on top of that.
Bake until the apple is soft and the pie dough is a nice golden brown.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix with cheese cubes.
Mix 1/2 stick oleo with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking dish.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix Bisquick with water until soft dough forms.
Pat in pan, pressing dough 1/2 up sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper in pan.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion; put on top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until edges of dough are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into thin slices. Cut ham into bite size pieces.
Melt butter. Stir in flour until blended.
Cook and slowly stir in milk.
Season with salt and paprika.
Pour mixture over mixed potatoes and ham in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
The potatoes may be turned with a spoon while cooking to insure even baking.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; cut up orange slices and mix with pineapple.
Sprinkle jello over top.
Stir in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour into mold.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter corn flakes balls
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Form into balls.
Place on waxed paper until completely cooled.

title: makes its own crust quick cobbler
directions: In a 9-inch baking dish, spray with pan spray.
Pour melted butter in dish.
Combine all ingredients together.
Put in dish. Pour fruit over ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes until crust comes to top and covers fruit with a light brown topping.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain. Cook chicken until well done.
Arrange broccoli in deep dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Arrange chicken in pieces on top of broccoli.
Stir together soup, water, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly and light brown.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and milk in pan.
Stir 10 to 15 minutes, constantly, until it thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: In food processor, coarsely chop cranberries; stir in sugar. Cover and chill 4 hours.
Drain cranberries for about 2 hours.
In large bowl, stir together remaining ingredients and gently stir in drained cranberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tony chachere's creole seasoning
directions: Mix well and use like salt. Store in an airtight jar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and make into a ball, about 1-inch, and press down with a fork.
Bake at 300°.
Watch carefully because they burn easily.

title: poor man's smoked salmon
directions: Carefully and thoroughly wash the sea lettuce to remove sand and other substances.
Sea lettuce may be used raw and added to tossed salads, added to seafood chowders or cooked.
When cooking, drop sea lettuce into boiling, salted water.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain.
Serve with butter, seafood salt or vinegar to taste.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into 2-quart greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, sugar, salt and flour.
Blend well, then stir eggs into mixture and add melted margarine.
Drop batter by tablespoonful on greased griddle or skillet.
Cook until brown on both sides.

title: salmon chowder for a crock-pot
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot, setting temperature on high for 1 hour, then reduce the heat to low and cook for 7 to 8 hours.

title: taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Crunch all chips in bag until bite size. Line 1/2 of chips on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix together chicken, mushroom soup, enchilada sauce, onion and garlic. Pour mixture over chips. Cover with 2 cups cheese. Place balance of crumbled chips on top.

title: melt-in-your-mouth cheese balls
directions: Mix Mozzarella cheese, 4 ounces flour, eggs, chives and cayenne pepper together.
Shape mixture into balls and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Combine flour and bread crumbs or cornflour.
Roll balls in mixture and refrigerate 10 minutes.
Place refrigerated balls 4 to 5 at a time in hot oil.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels and serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Divide mixture into thirds.
Spoon each third onto an ungreased cookie sheet, spreading into an 8 1/2-inch circle.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen 10-inch cookies.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high 8 hours without lid.
Stir occasionally.
After 5 hours adjust spices to taste.
Can in pint jars.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: beverly's sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Alternate adding eggs and flour.
(Add salt and soda with first cup of flour.)
Add sour cream, then vanilla last.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: english pea salad
directions: In a deep dish, layer the first 6 ingredients.
Spread over peas the mayonnaise mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Just before serving, add the remaining ingredients in layers.

title: turtle cheese cake
directions: Combine and pat in spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mint cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler. Add peppermint oil to taste.
Dip Ritz crackers in chocolate and lay flat on waxed paper until hard.
Store in cool place in tightly closed container. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Drain.
Add onions, cabbage and celery. Cook until vegetables are light brown.
Stir in tomatoes and kidney beans with juice liquid, water, salt, pepper and chili powder. Heat 10 minutes at boiling point.
Reduce heat.

title: oven smothered chicken
directions: Place chicken parts in a large casserole dish. Sprinkle all dry ingredients over chicken. Spread soup over chicken and pour Coke over entire chicken. Cut up margarine in pats over the chicken. Cover and place in 400° oven for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake another 15 minutes. Remove cover and brown chicken on both sides, allowing the sauce to thicken. Serve over rice.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, then drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add beans last.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown in hot fat.
Place sliced potatoes in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Salt and pepper potatoes to taste.
Arrange browned pork chops on top of potatoes.
Slice onion on top of chops.
Pour soup over onion.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, depending on thickness of chops.
Soup makes delicious gravy on potatoes as it cooks.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix together and press into an 8 x 10-inch casserole.
Bake until light brown.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and add 1 stick of margarine; set aside. Cream sugar and 1 stick of butter.
Add eggs.
Add alternately the flour and soda with milk.
Add melted candy bars and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Fry bacon and onion over low heat until onion is transparent and bacon is crisp.
In Dutch oven, add bacon ad onion.
Add the tomatoes and okra, salt, black pepper and oregano.
Add sugar, bouillon cubes and water.
Simmer slowly about 2 hours.
Add 1 cup cooked rice.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer 15 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: *If cake mix does not have pudding in it, add 1 package of coconut or vanilla instant pudding.

title: margaret's cucumber pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, alum and salt with vinegar and let stand 2 months.
After 2 months drain all vinegar off cucumbers.
Cover with 10 cups of sugar and 2 teaspoons pickling spices in cloth. Let stand 2 weeks.
Ready to eat.
(Keep adding sugar until 10 cups are used.)

title: banana cream pie
directions: Put an	unopened
can
of Eagle Brand milk in a pan and cover it	with water.
Put on stove and let it slow
boil
for 1 1/2 hours.
Just
before
it finishes cooking, slice 2 or 3 thin layers of bananas into a graham cracker crust.
Carefully punch a hole
in
the
can	to
let
steam	escape	and
then immediately open
the
can and pour onto the bananas.
Let it slightly cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli until tender; drain. Combine remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Mix with broccoli.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: iron skillet pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in small mixing bowl.
Melt butter in an iron skillet; add sugar mixture.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and beat together.
Add a little at a time to mixture in skillet. Stir constantly.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.

title: gourmet cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage, celery, green pepper and onion until tender. Put in buttered casserole and stir in cheese sauce or cheese soup. Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 375° for ten minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter bread slices, cut into 2-inch squares and put these into casserole dish.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Pour over bread, mix thoroughly so that bread absorbs egg mixture and is mashed together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: With 1 cup water, add salt and cook onions and zucchini for 10 minutes.
Layer in baking dish and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all but the chick peas; add chick peas to beans.
Add 1 red onion, shredded and 1/2 cup shredded green pepper.
Mix thoroughly in a separate bowl and add to beans, onion and pepper.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Salt to taste.
Cook noodles separately and drain.
Add all other ingredients except cheese to meat. Alternately place a layer of the meat mixture and then a layer of noodles in casserole dish until full.
Top with cheese slices. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until light brown and bubbly.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Mix all together.
Crumble bacon on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
A deep, heavy bean pot takes a little longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together to blend.
Roll out on floured board and cut to desired size; place on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° in preheated oven for 12-15 minutes.

title: hamburger roast(good, quick and easy)
directions: Rub frozen ground beef with molasses or syrup and place in heavy iron skillet.
Sprinkle well with pepper and garlic salt. Put strips of bacon on top of roast.
Place sliced vegetables around meat.
Cover only the vegetables with V-8 juice.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° to 400° or until done.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, over simmering water, place egg yolks and water; beat until well blended and lemon colored.
Stir in lemon juice.
Beat in butter, a few pieces at a time.
Beat until sauce is smooth.
Stir in salt.
Serve at once.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Combine ground beef and spaghetti sauce.
Lay 3 noodles side by side in bottom of baking dish.
Measure out 1 1/3 cups of meat sauce and sprinkle over noodles, smoothing out over the noodles so it pretty much covers the noodles.
Take half of cottage cheese mixture and spoon it over the meat sauce in 5 or 6 clumps.
Use the fork to smooth this out so it covers the meat sauce.
Repeat for 2nd layer.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Prepare bottom crust by mixing together the flour, butter and nuts until crumblike.
Press mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown. Cool.
Beat cream cheese with sugar until smooth.
Fold in cake pan.
Spread mixture over cool crust.
Combine vanilla and chocolate pudding mixes; beat in milk until smooth and thickened. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, onion dip, cheese and pepper.
Add partially thawed potatoes (thawed enough so they can be separated).
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Pour melted butter over top of corn flakes.

title: the magic pickle
directions: Drain pickles.
Put spices and vinegar in the pickle jar.
Add pickles and pour over sugar.
Do not stir.
Close jar and shake to dissolve sugar.
After those are eaten, add another quart of pickles and 1 more cup of sugar.
These are sweet and delicious.

title: grandma mccray's broccoli casserole
directions: Melt cheese and margarine. Mix broccoli (semi-frozen), rice and undiluted soup in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour in hot water. Add most of cheese and margarine.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour remaining cheese mixture over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: guilt free roasted potatoes
directions: Wash and drain potatoes, then cut into lengthwise quarters. Combine cheese and spices on large paper plate.
Press cut surfaces of potatoes firmly into mixture.
Place potato slices, cut sides down, on a vegetable oil sprayed cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Roast potatoes in 350° oven for 30 minutes and then turn so other cut side of potato is on cookie sheet with a metal spatula and cook 30 more minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: homemade halloween makeup ii(child-approved)
directions: Mix shortening, cornstarch and your color choice of food coloring.
For red makeup, use 2 drops red.
For brown, use 2 drops green and 1 drop red.
For purple, use 1 drop blue and 2 red.
Once made, the makeup can be stored in small jars.
This is non-toxic and comes right off.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place the chicken breasts in a baking dish and brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt substitute and garlic powder.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain the excess fat and juice from the chicken.
Brush the apricot jam on each piece of chicken with a pastry brush.
Return to the oven and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: my family's favorite pot roast
directions: Sprinkle beef with flour, coating all sides.
Brown 15 to 20 minutes in fat in heavy kettle or Dutch oven over moderate heat. Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper as it browns.
Add oregano, vinegar, lemon, onion and tomatoes.
Cover pot tightly and let simmer over low heat.
Turn roast occasionally.
Cook 3 1/2 hours.

title: italian anise cookies
directions: Melt Crisco and reserve.
Beat eggs and sugar; add melted Crisco and milk.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well. This makes a fairly firm dough.
Shape as desired.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with white icing; dip in colored sugar.

title: jello salad(low-fat)
directions: Follow instructions on jello box.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate until set.
Great.

title: bread and butter pickles(sandwich pickles)
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and cooking salt and cover with water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed. Add drained vegetables and just bring to a boil.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and flour in a baking dish.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until light brown.

title: peach preserves
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar with peaches, lemon juice and butter.
Boil 10 minutes and add the other 2 cups of sugar. Cook 15 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Mix until Jell-O is dissolved.
Let cool.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well and form into balls.

title: hawaiian butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt on wax paper.
Set aside. Cream sugar, butter and egg together.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in butterscotch chips, pineapple, nuts and orange rind.
Mix completely.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack. Yields about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Add shortening and milk and beat 2 minutes (300 strokes).
Add eggs and vanilla and beat 2 more minutes.
Put in walnuts and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375° in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or three 9-inch layers.
Cool and frost.
All ingredients should be room temperature.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: peacheesy pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients to make one pie crust.
Roll out and line a 9-inch pie plate with it.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, mix and butter.
Mix well.
Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chocolate pieces over crust.
Top with melted caramel.
Top with teaspoons of remaining cake mixture.
Press gently into caramel. Sprinkle with nuts.
Press lightly into top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pasta with peppers and shrimp
directions: Strain marinade from artichokes and pour with olive oil into pan.
Saute peppers until limp.
While they are cooking, boil water in another big pot and cook pasta al dente.
When peppers are cooked, add garlic, olives, shrimp, salt and red pepper flakes.
Saute until garlic is cooked.
When pasta is cooked, drain and toss with contents of pan along with artichokes, cheese and lemon juice.
Season with freshly ground pepper.
Serves 4.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Place 2 slices of dried beef around chicken breast.
Wrap 1 slice of bacon around it and secure with a toothpick.
Place rolls in an ungreased baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken rolls.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add sugar and stir.
Add milk and stir.
Roll out biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in bottom of 9x13 pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, butter, salt, powder, flour and milk together and spread over fruit.
Mix 1 cup sugar and corn starch; spread over batter.
Pour water over the top of sugar and batter.

title: simpsons' chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large pot.
Add salt, pepper, and chili powder, and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients, except beans.
Simmer about 30 minutes, then add beans and heat.
Thicken with flour and water if desired.
Serve topped with grated cheese.

title: easy mexicali dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet or Dutch oven; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in noodles, tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 cup shredded cheese, olives and seasonings.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: kielbasa and pineapple
directions: Cut kielbasa into bite size pieces and put into microwave dish or bowl.
Add pineapple and enough barbecue sauce to coat evenly. Microwave on Full power for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir after first 10 minutes and then again before serving.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread crushed corn chips in bottom of pan (save 1 cup).
Add chicken.
Mix soup, chiles, sour cream and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Top with remaining chips and tomatoes.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices together and pour into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over the mix then the nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 24 squares.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour can of peaches with juice into bottom of an 8 x 13-inch pan. (May use extra small can sliced peaches if thicker cobbler desired.)
Melt butter in microwave or stove top and mix with entire cake mix.
Crumble on top of peaches in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
